00:12:30,279 --> 00:12:32,199
WENGER:
It was a monocultural team.

169
00:12:33,079 --> 00:12:34,719
An English block of players

170
00:12:34,999 --> 00:12:37,599
with one star in there,
Dennis Bergkamp.

171
00:12:38,159 --> 00:12:39,159
Ooh!

172
00:12:40,039 --> 00:12:41,959
DENNIS BERGKAMP:
What he has said from day one

173
00:12:42,039 --> 00:12:44,559
"You shouldn't take
the English mentality

174
00:12:44,639 --> 00:12:45,919
out of an English team".

175
00:12:46,439 --> 00:12:48,319
That's what he taught

176
00:12:49,239 --> 00:12:51,519
and expected from
the foreign players as well.

177
00:12:51,599 --> 00:12:52,999
To have that mentality.

178
00:12:53,479 --> 00:12:55,159
TONY ADAMS:
I ain't got time for transitions.

179
00:12:55,439 --> 00:12:56,919
I don't like that word.

180
00:12:56,999 --> 00:12:58,319
It's a type of excuse.

181
00:12:58,559 --> 00:13:00,199
Look at him. Look at the camera.

182
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:03,559
WENGER: They were a group
of very strong personalities.

183
00:13:03,679 --> 00:13:04,719
Nice one.
- I love you, Dicko.

184
00:13:04,799 --> 00:13:05,679
I love you too.

185
00:13:05,799 --> 00:13:07,399
WENGER:
A group of men.

186
00:13:09,439 --> 00:13:10,999
They were not always easy.

187
00:13:11,919 --> 00:13:13,199
But on Saturday...

188
00:13:14,279 --> 00:13:15,759
you could walk out with them.

189
00:13:16,799 --> 00:13:18,639
You knew they were ready
for a fight.

190
00:13:19,279 --> 00:13:20,519
CROWD CLAMORS

191
00:13:21,439 --> 00:13:23,399
CROWD ROARS

192
00:13:24,359 --> 00:13:25,959
And I'm not singing
"1-0" no more.

193
00:13:27,599 --> 00:13:30,119
INDISTINCT CHATTER

194
00:13:32,799 --> 00:13:34,799
LEE DIXON:
His biggest asset on the training ground

195
00:13:34,879 --> 00:13:37,039
was allowing his players

196
00:13:37,559 --> 00:13:40,519
to express themselves
and work problems out on the pitch.

197
00:13:40,599 --> 00:13:42,359
Good ball, yes.

198
00:13:45,119 --> 00:13:46,879
MARTIN KEOWN: By the time
you reach 30 years of age

199
00:13:47,559 --> 00:13:49,559
you've kind of set out your character,
haven't you?

200
00:13:49,639 --> 00:13:51,799
As how you wanna play football
and how you see it...

201
00:13:52,879 --> 00:13:54,359
and when Wenger arrived

202
00:13:54,799 --> 00:13:57,399
he gave a renaissance, really,
for that group.

203
00:13:59,439 --> 00:14:00,919
WENGER:
There was a drinking culture.

204
00:14:02,399 --> 00:14:05,479
I always felt it's stupid
to work the whole week in training

205
00:14:05,759 --> 00:14:07,799
and then to kill yourself
outside the pitch.

206
00:14:09,559 --> 00:14:10,759
I cut that all off.

207
00:14:11,479 --> 00:14:13,039
They had to change their habits.

208
00:14:16,879 --> 00:14:18,639
WRIGHT:
It changed from night to day.

209
00:14:19,719 --> 00:14:22,319
No tea, no sugar, nothing.

210
00:14:22,479 --> 00:14:25,079
All you could drink was water
and the food what was provided.

211
00:14:26,919 --> 00:14:29,439
Changed it to suit us, so we ain't got
no butter or anything in it.

212
00:14:30,239 --> 00:14:33,239
BERGKAMP: Immediately we had success
with his way of thinking.

213
00:14:33,559 --> 00:14:35,639
That made the English players realise

214
00:14:35,719 --> 00:14:38,279
"OK, wait a minute,
this is what we want".

215
00:14:38,359 --> 00:14:40,159
We didn't know if it was
the stretching

216
00:14:40,719 --> 00:14:43,519
it was the vitamins we were taking

217
00:14:43,959 --> 00:14:45,079
it was the new diet.

218
00:14:45,239 --> 00:14:46,559
We felt like supermen.

219
00:14:51,719 --> 00:14:54,479
WENGER:
Every win gave me a bit of time.

220
00:14:57,479 --> 00:14:59,119
But when you started to win

221
00:14:59,959 --> 00:15:02,759
it created some adverse reactions.

222
00:15:04,879 --> 00:15:06,159
Private attacks.

223
00:15:07,279 --> 00:15:08,479
Vicious attacks.

224
00:15:13,119 --> 00:15:15,439
I visited my parents in Strasbourg...

225
00:15:16,519 --> 00:15:18,439
and when I came back, I took a cab

226
00:15:18,839 --> 00:15:20,999
and he told me,
"Why did you resign?"

227
00:15:22,359 --> 00:15:23,839
I said, "Who told you that?"

228
00:15:24,039 --> 00:15:25,959
REPORTER:
He arrived just seven weeks ago...

229
00:15:26,399 --> 00:15:28,239
WENGER: He said,
"It's been announced on the radio."

230
00:15:28,639 --> 00:15:29,919
...but now he's at the center

231
00:15:29,999 --> 00:15:32,519
of suggestions about
his own personal life.

232
00:15:34,919 --> 00:15:37,599
PRESS OFFICER: ...from ITN, they'll be
asking you a couple of questions.

233
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:40,759
WENGER: So I had to
improvise a press conference

234
00:15:41,119 --> 00:15:44,279
on the stairs in front of Highbury...

235
00:15:44,359 --> 00:15:47,519
JOURNALIST:

236
00:15:47,599 --> 00:15:48,639
Sorry?

237
00:15:48,959 --> 00:15:50,679
...to say "I have not resigned.

238
00:15:50,799 --> 00:15:52,679
You know, if you have anything
against me

239
00:15:52,959 --> 00:15:53,999
bring it out...

240
00:15:54,359 --> 00:15:55,999
and let's deal with it."

241
00:15:56,759 --> 00:16:00,119
JOURNALIST:

242
00:16:00,239 --> 00:16:01,279
No.

243
00:16:02,719 --> 00:16:04,759
WRIGHT:
This obviously started from nothing

244
00:16:04,959 --> 00:16:06,919
but he had to come out
and say something.

245
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:11,119
It really was so callous and nasty.

246
00:16:11,639 --> 00:16:14,319
JOURNALIST:

247
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:22,559
HE LAUGHS

248
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:25,239
"Oh, we have photos
that are very bad for you."

249
00:16:25,919 --> 00:16:28,879
Bring me somebody who can speak
about my private life.

250
00:16:28,959 --> 00:16:30,919
! have a private life, like everybody,
like you.

251
00:16:31,479 --> 00:16:33,279
Of course, they had nothing.

252
00:16:35,759 --> 00:16:37,559
WRIGHT:
There was a massive negativity

253
00:16:37,639 --> 00:16:39,199
because he was a foreign manager

254
00:16:39,879 --> 00:16:42,679
and he was doing stuff
that was alien to everybody.

255
00:16:44,519 --> 00:16:46,559
People are afraid of things
that's different.

256
00:16:47,159 --> 00:16:49,879
The natural thing to do is
to try and find fault

257
00:16:49,999 --> 00:16:52,039
and try and create, um...

258
00:16:52,799 --> 00:16:53,759
a problem.

259
00:16:53,879 --> 00:16:55,519
What have you concrete?

260
00:16:55,719 --> 00:16:57,039
From me, my life?

261
00:16:57,119 --> 00:16:58,759
What do you know of my life
concretely?

262
00:17:00,079 --> 00:17:01,879
JOURNALIST: We don't know anything.
- But... But...

263
00:17:02,199 --> 00:17:04,719
JOURNALISTS CLAMOR

264
00:17:04,799 --> 00:17:06,119
Thank you very much.

265
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:08,959
BYSTANDERS CHEER AND APPLAUD

266
00:17:13,559 --> 00:17:16,639
SIREN BLARES

267
00:17:17,359 --> 00:17:18,759
HORN HONKS

268
00:17:24,639 --> 00:17:29,039
MAN IN FRENCH:
— PATRICK VIEIRA IN FRENCH:

269
00:17:30,559 --> 00:17:33,719
WENGER: Patrick was known
as a big talent in France

270
00:17:33,879 --> 00:17:37,199
and considering that he was only 20...

271
00:17:38,439 --> 00:17:40,959
it was a big chance for Arsenal
to take this player.

272
00:17:42,719 --> 00:17:44,759
WENGER: First of all...
- PHOTOGRAPHER: Ready?

273
00:17:45,119 --> 00:17:46,759
...you couldn't impress him.

274
00:17:46,879 --> 00:17:47,839
<i>Ready to go.</i>

275
00:17:48,999 --> 00:17:50,839
WENGER:
He wasn't scared of anybody.

276
00:17:54,839 --> 00:17:56,719
VIEIRA:
Nobody knew who I was.

277
00:17:58,039 --> 00:18:01,719
This tall guy has come in,
really skinny and have this kind of...

278
00:18:02,439 --> 00:18:03,919
strange way of running.

279
00:18:06,679 --> 00:18:09,879
But from the first game
that I played with the first team

280
00:18:12,279 --> 00:18:15,079
I convince my teammates

281
00:18:15,159 --> 00:18:18,959
that I can play in this club
and I can play on that level.

282
00:18:19,999 --> 00:18:21,479
COMMENTATOR:
Here's Vieira...

283
00:18:21,599 --> 00:18:22,719
it's a great run...

284
00:18:22,999 --> 00:18:24,119
<i>he's still going...</i>

285
00:18:24,359 --> 00:18:27,439
WRIGHT: His first touch,
his skills, his running with the ball...

286
00:18:28,839 --> 00:18:29,839
THEY LAUGH

287
00:18:29,919 --> 00:18:32,799
"Jesus Christ, that's our player!"

288
00:18:34,759 --> 00:18:37,159
VIEIRA:
Arséne of course was really important

289
00:18:37,319 --> 00:18:39,599
he gave me that confidence
to express myself.

290
00:18:40,559 --> 00:18:42,719
WENGER:
Everybody thought maybe the manager

291
00:18:42,799 --> 00:18:45,679
doesn't know what he's doing,
but at least he brings a good player!

292
00:18:46,479 --> 00:18:49,119
And I did bring a good player.
I brought a hell of a player, you know?

293
00:18:51,439 --> 00:18:53,039
CROWD ROARS

294
00:18:53,119 --> 00:18:57,039
VIEIRA IN FRENCH:

295
00:19:04,119 --> 00:19:06,119
BELL CHIMES

296
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:13,519
TONY BLAIR:
And this New Labour government

297
00:19:13,959 --> 00:19:18,679
will govern in the interests of all
our people, the whole of this nation.

298
00:19:18,839 --> 00:19:20,239
PEOPLE CHEER

299
00:19:20,439 --> 00:19:22,359
WENGER:
From '97 onwards

300
00:19:22,999 --> 00:19:26,679
England became more open
to the rest of the world.

301
00:19:32,479 --> 00:19:35,399
London became very cosmopolitan.

302
00:19:37,399 --> 00:19:40,999
It coincided with the start
of an evolution in the English game.

303
00:19:41,479 --> 00:19:43,199
JOURNALIST:
Was it a penalty on Sunday?

304
00:19:43,279 --> 00:19:45,039
Ah, no chance, man.
The referee was a cheat.

305
00:19:45,199 --> 00:19:46,479
PEOPLE LAUGH

306
00:19:47,079 --> 00:19:48,959
WENGER:
The '97-'98 season

307
00:19:49,319 --> 00:19:52,479
you could see there was something there
that was blossoming.

308
00:19:55,159 --> 00:19:57,639
There was an old core
of English players

309
00:19:58,039 --> 00:20:00,039
and a new clique
of foreign players.

310
00:20:02,159 --> 00:20:04,119
I brought Emmanuel Petit in.

311
00:20:04,199 --> 00:20:05,079
Morning.

312
00:20:05,159 --> 00:20:07,879
WENGER: He was a more defensive
player than Patrick Vieira

313
00:20:08,399 --> 00:20:10,719
so the two together, of course,
were two monsters.

314
00:20:10,879 --> 00:20:12,519
THEY LAUGH

315
00:20:13,119 --> 00:20:16,159
And I bought a super player
in called Marc Overmars.

316
00:20:18,719 --> 00:20:19,999
CROWD ROARS

317
00:20:21,039 --> 00:20:25,319
IN FRENCH:

318
00:20:25,559 --> 00:20:27,559
Nicholas Anelka... wow.

319
00:20:27,759 --> 00:20:29,799
WRIGHT: He was just like
an unstoppable force.

320
00:20:32,679 --> 00:20:33,799
CROWD CHEERS

321
00:20:33,879 --> 00:20:36,399
KEOWN: I'd never seen
a 17-year-old kid that good.

322
00:20:36,959 --> 00:20:39,879
It was that sort of feeling
of almost giggling

323
00:20:40,159 --> 00:20:41,359
at the quality.

324
00:20:43,679 --> 00:20:44,799
CROWD CHEERS

325
00:20:44,879 --> 00:20:46,519
Really high-calibre players.

326
00:20:46,879 --> 00:20:48,599
But they've all been bought
by Arséne Wenger.

327
00:20:50,679 --> 00:20:52,679
I'm the king of the world!

328
00:20:57,359 --> 00:20:58,639
WENGER:
In the Championship

329
00:20:58,799 --> 00:21:01,799
we were nine points
behind Man United.

330
00:21:05,719 --> 00:21:08,359
But the whole team was convinced
that we could win it.

331
00:21:16,559 --> 00:21:17,799
COMMENTATOR:
Oh, it's Overmars!

332
00:21:19,599 --> 00:21:20,639
He's done it!

333
00:21:21,639 --> 00:21:24,959
The Championship race is
still wide open!

334
00:21:27,959 --> 00:21:31,519
COMMENTATOR 2: And Sheffield Wednesday
wonder quite what has hit them.

335
00:21:32,279 --> 00:21:35,199
WRIGHT: He was very different
because every other manager

336
00:21:35,439 --> 00:21:36,679
even if you're doing well

337
00:21:37,039 --> 00:21:38,119
they have to blast you down.

338
00:21:40,159 --> 00:21:41,119
CROWD CHEERS

339
00:21:41,439 --> 00:21:42,439
He didn't do that.

340
00:21:43,519 --> 00:21:46,759
COMMENTATOR: Three against Newcastle,
four against Blackburn

341
00:21:46,839 --> 00:21:49,319
and now five against Wimbledon.

342
00:21:51,439 --> 00:21:53,999
You could see people were
fearing us. They feared us.

343
00:21:55,359 --> 00:21:56,599
COMMENTATOR:
So close now.

344
00:21:57,759 --> 00:22:00,359
Arsenal chase the one win needed.

345
00:22:01,919 --> 00:22:05,639
The intensity of the experience
was something that was unbelievable.

346
00:22:06,119 --> 00:22:09,679
FANS CHANT:
Arsenal! Arsenal!

347
00:22:11,039 --> 00:22:16,879
I'll never forget, Tony Adams scored at
Highbury on a sunny afternoon in May.

348
00:22:17,839 --> 00:22:19,839
COMMENTATOR:
Adams, put through by Bould!

349
00:22:20,319 --> 00:22:22,159
Would you believe it?

350
00:22:23,559 --> 00:22:25,199
FINAL WHISTLE BLOWS

351
00:22:25,279 --> 00:22:26,959
Ten straight wins.

352
00:22:27,639 --> 00:22:30,239
They've absolutely roared
to the title.

353
00:22:31,439 --> 00:22:33,839
CROWD ROARS

354
00:22:39,039 --> 00:22:41,239
Yeah! What's this?

355
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:42,799
Hey!
- MAN: Hey!

356
00:22:43,039 --> 00:22:44,199
Where'd that come from?

357
00:22:45,039 --> 00:22:47,759
INTERVIEWER: It's difficult to realise
what a Frenchman's done over here.

358
00:22:48,679 --> 00:22:51,079
I hadn't even heard of you, actually,
I've gotta be honest about that.

359
00:22:51,559 --> 00:22:54,839
And now we're faced with the prospect
that you could do the double.

360
00:22:55,079 --> 00:22:57,359
CROWD CHANTS INDISTINCTLY

361
00:23:02,159 --> 00:23:05,039
WENGER: This was a defining moment
of my career at Arsenal.

362
00:23:08,639 --> 00:23:10,679
An exceptional moment in my life.

363
00:23:13,199 --> 00:23:16,039
To win straightaway
was absolutely vital.

364
00:23:16,879 --> 00:23:18,799
COMMENTATOR: Here's Overmars,
could be there for the Dutchman

365
00:23:18,879 --> 00:23:20,959
<i>he's through here...
and he's scored!</i>

366
00:23:21,439 --> 00:23:22,879
Boom-boom. The double.

367
00:23:24,399 --> 00:23:25,759
COMMENTATOR:
Anelka's away!

368
00:23:26,239 --> 00:23:27,319
Good strike!

369
00:23:27,519 --> 00:23:29,199
CROWD CHEERS

370
00:23:31,279 --> 00:23:33,119
WENGER:
I could come, unknown

371
00:23:33,399 --> 00:23:35,559
and win as a French guy.

372
00:23:35,719 --> 00:23:39,319
CROWD CLAMORS
- HORNS TOOT

373
00:23:42,999 --> 00:23:46,679
It was a very long honeymoon
and it was the start of it.

374
00:23:48,879 --> 00:23:49,959
The real start of it.

375
00:23:55,239 --> 00:23:56,839
HE YELLS

376
00:23:59,559 --> 00:24:01,239
MAN ON ADVERT:
Is this your idea of luxury?

377
00:24:02,199 --> 00:24:05,119
There's a hint of history
and wealth in every street-side symbol.

378
00:24:05,799 --> 00:24:08,519
But this is the fairy-tale land
which flirts with the business world.

379
00:24:08,759 --> 00:24:09,999
Yes, this is Monaco.

380
00:24:13,999 --> 00:24:17,159
WENGER: Monaco, it was the first time
I realised that I could win.

381
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:20,879
I was 36, 37.

382
00:24:22,639 --> 00:24:24,719
In my first season,
we won the Championship.

383
00:24:25,119 --> 00:24:26,439
COMMENTATOR IN FRENCH:
Balle de match!

384
00:24:26,719 --> 00:24:27,919
Et but!

385
00:24:28,559 --> 00:24:31,479
But I won it with
some English players, Mark Hateley

386
00:24:31,839 --> 00:24:34,279
and the super Glenn Hoddle.

387
00:24:37,839 --> 00:24:42,239
JOURNALIST IN FRENCH:

388
00:24:42,439 --> 00:24:44,999
IN FRENCH:

389
00:24:45,919 --> 00:24:47,399
WENGER:
Marseille had a fantastic team

390
00:24:47,639 --> 00:24:49,079
IN FRENCH:

391
00:24:53,439 --> 00:24:54,759
JOURNALIST LAUGHS

392
00:24:58,599 --> 00:25:00,759
WENGER:
But the rumors were there.

393
00:25:01,439 --> 00:25:02,839
The suspicion was there.

394
00:25:04,359 --> 00:25:06,839
DIXON:
That period at Monaco was hard for him.

395
00:25:07,319 --> 00:25:09,799
There was some allegations
of match-fixing.

396
00:25:10,359 --> 00:25:11,359
Corruption.

397
00:25:12,319 --> 00:25:13,799
WENGER:
It ended badly.

398
00:25:13,879 --> 00:25:16,479
NEWS PRESENTER IN FRENCH:

399
00:25:24,359 --> 00:25:26,199
WENGER:
Marseille was relegated.

400
00:25:27,319 --> 00:25:29,079
It was a dark period
of French football.

401
00:25:30,119 --> 00:25:31,999
MAN ON ADVERT:
<i>Is this still your idea of luxury?</i>

402
00:25:32,079 --> 00:25:34,799
Or has the commercial clamor
destroyed completely the memories...

403
00:25:35,759 --> 00:25:36,599
HE EXHALES

404
00:25:37,039 --> 00:25:39,079
What is absolutely unbelievable

405
00:25:39,639 --> 00:25:42,799
it didn't stop my belief
in human beings.

406
00:25:46,399 --> 00:25:48,639
Not being capable to trust other people

407
00:25:48,879 --> 00:25:50,759
you would be unhappy your whole life.

408
00:25:55,639 --> 00:25:57,959
I had done ten years
in French football

409
00:25:59,079 --> 00:26:02,519
and I thought, "It's time
for me to go somewhere else."

410
00:26:15,679 --> 00:26:16,959
WENGER:
And this is the name.

411
00:26:18,199 --> 00:26:20,439
<i>Arséne Wenger.
— Ah! Arséne!</i>

412
00:26:22,839 --> 00:26:23,679
WENGER:
You?

413
00:26:23,799 --> 00:26:24,999
THEY LAUGH

414
00:26:25,079 --> 00:26:28,119
WENGER: You have some managers
who are exportable...

415
00:26:29,119 --> 00:26:30,359
and some not.

416
00:26:32,319 --> 00:26:39,239
IN FRENCH:

417
00:26:39,759 --> 00:26:42,439
It's adaptation
to a different way of living.

418
00:26:42,999 --> 00:26:44,839
That's not always easy.

419
00:26:45,599 --> 00:26:48,199
WENGER IN FRENCH:

420
00:27:11,399 --> 00:27:13,759
WENGER: I took a team who was
bottom of the league...

421
00:27:14,919 --> 00:27:18,839
MAN IN JAPANESE ON RADIO:

422
00:27:20,879 --> 00:27:23,119
...we finished second in the league
and won the cup.

423
00:27:23,959 --> 00:27:26,319
I was straightaway Manager of The Year.

424
00:27:30,519 --> 00:27:33,999
WENGER IN FRENCH:

425
00:27:41,959 --> 00:27:43,039
WENGER:
Yeah, better.

426
00:27:43,439 --> 00:27:48,039
I was keen to go somewhere and show
that I have the talent.

427
00:27:49,639 --> 00:27:52,599
I thought,
"I can cope with going abroad".

428
00:27:52,839 --> 00:27:53,959
WHISTLE BLOWS

429
00:27:56,599 --> 00:27:57,799
Yeah!

430
00:27:58,519 --> 00:27:59,639
You see! You see!

431
00:28:01,479 --> 00:28:03,679
WOMAN SQUEALS

432
00:28:04,719 --> 00:28:06,599
Come on!
- HE YELLS IN JAPANESE

433
00:28:07,639 --> 00:28:10,959
I could have decided to stay
in Japan for a long period.

434
00:28:12,879 --> 00:28:16,239
But I thought I'd come back to Europe
if it's for a big club.

435
00:28:18,519 --> 00:28:20,719
I had a clear idea of what I wanted...

436
00:28:21,559 --> 00:28:24,279
and I knew quickly
what I could bring in.

437
00:28:25,439 --> 00:28:28,079
CHILDREN SHOUT
- DRUMS THUD

438
00:28:44,559 --> 00:28:46,759
WENGER:
It's nice through the trees around there.

439
00:28:47,719 --> 00:28:48,839
Unbelievable.

440
00:28:50,759 --> 00:28:52,279
DEIN:
Normality's boring, isn't it?

441
00:28:54,279 --> 00:28:56,559
The way he lives his life
is not normal.

442
00:28:58,079 --> 00:28:59,119
WENGER:
I'm a hermit.

443
00:29:01,559 --> 00:29:04,439
In fact, at night,
I sleep in the tree there.

444
00:29:07,639 --> 00:29:08,679
DEIN:
He was driven.

445
00:29:09,039 --> 00:29:10,119
Wonderfully driven.

446
00:29:10,399 --> 00:29:11,479
I mean, so focused.

447
00:29:13,879 --> 00:29:15,719
WENGER:
I lived in my bubble.

448
00:29:17,199 --> 00:29:18,559
My own little world.

449
00:29:25,479 --> 00:29:30,879
IN FRENCH:

450
00:29:34,879 --> 00:29:36,919
I had only a triangle:

451
00:29:37,239 --> 00:29:40,199
Home, training center, Highbury.

452
00:29:43,279 --> 00:29:45,999
I prepare the game
exactly like a player.

453
00:29:49,039 --> 00:29:51,759
I never go out 48 hours
before a game.

454
00:29:52,039 --> 00:29:53,719
For dinner, or anything.

455
00:29:57,039 --> 00:29:59,079
You have to sacrifice your life
for this job.

456
00:30:00,919 --> 00:30:02,479
PHONE RINGS

457
00:30:08,719 --> 00:30:09,719
Hello?

458
00:30:10,879 --> 00:30:12,239
Arséne...

459
00:30:13,319 --> 00:30:17,679
IN FRENCH:

460
00:30:19,959 --> 00:30:21,159
...One or two shirts.

461
00:30:21,239 --> 00:30:22,719
No problem.
- I tell you tomorrow.

462
00:30:22,799 --> 00:30:23,679
OK.

463
00:30:35,519 --> 00:30:37,239
WENGER:
People say "obsession"...

464
00:30:37,999 --> 00:30:38,959
but for me...

465
00:30:39,799 --> 00:30:42,359
I cannot even tell you
it was work, I loved it.

466
00:30:45,759 --> 00:30:48,879
DEIN: First thing I did
was to get a couple of satellites for him

467
00:30:49,239 --> 00:30:51,559
so that he had games coming in
from all over the world.

468
00:30:51,959 --> 00:30:54,199
COMMENTATOR SPEAKS GERMAN

469
00:30:54,519 --> 00:30:57,079
WENGER:
Germany, Spain, Italy, France...

470
00:30:58,119 --> 00:31:01,839
every night was football, football,
football and tomorrow, football again.

471
00:31:02,399 --> 00:31:03,279
Away!

472
00:31:03,439 --> 00:31:04,639
Players who will play...

473
00:31:04,959 --> 00:31:06,599
HE SIGHS

474
00:31:07,679 --> 00:31:09,959
He put everything into it.
He put his life and soul into it.

475
00:31:10,279 --> 00:31:11,199
David?

476
00:31:12,879 --> 00:31:14,719
I'm just leaving. I'm going home now.

477
00:31:16,279 --> 00:31:17,719
OK? So I'll see you later.

478
00:31:20,359 --> 00:31:21,359
I know.

479
00:31:28,519 --> 00:31:30,319
Ah, the writer's chair here.

480
00:31:30,759 --> 00:31:31,679
Right.

481
00:31:33,719 --> 00:31:36,199
PRODUCER: OK, Sir Alex Ferguson,
Manchester United manager.

482
00:31:36,479 --> 00:31:37,959
ALEX FERGUSON:
Always look in your rear mirror

483
00:31:38,039 --> 00:31:39,279
to see who's behind you.

484
00:31:40,279 --> 00:31:42,679
I mean, you see someone
come up behind you, you accelerate.

485
00:31:44,599 --> 00:31:47,399
Alex Ferguson was the dominant figure
in English football.

486
00:31:47,479 --> 00:31:50,239
Everybody was scared of him,
from the press to the referees.

487
00:31:50,359 --> 00:31:52,159
I've shown great patience with you.

488
00:31:52,599 --> 00:31:55,039
He was the guy to beat.
He was the don.

489
00:31:55,479 --> 00:31:57,119
<i>Arséne Wenger's been in Japan.</i>

490
00:31:57,359 --> 00:31:59,039
<i>He doesn't know anything
about English football.</i>

491
00:31:59,119 --> 00:32:00,799
He's unaware of the demands
of our game.

492
00:32:01,559 --> 00:32:03,879
WENGER: I thought that's
a good opportunity for me

493
00:32:03,959 --> 00:32:05,959
to show that
it's not only in England that...

494
00:32:06,959 --> 00:32:08,639
you know how to play football.

495
00:32:09,759 --> 00:32:11,279
I was ready for a fight.

496
00:32:12,759 --> 00:32:14,119
CROWD CHEERS

497
00:32:16,759 --> 00:32:18,039
Arsenal were catching us up

498
00:32:18,359 --> 00:32:20,839
and their team was good enough

499
00:32:21,439 --> 00:32:23,079
to go above us,
there's no question about that.

500
00:32:26,079 --> 00:32:28,239
WENGER:
It was sometimes very aggressive

501
00:32:28,319 --> 00:32:29,839
especially after the games.

502
00:32:30,119 --> 00:32:31,959
FERGUSON: Think he should
concentrate on his own job

503
00:32:32,039 --> 00:32:33,879
rather than talk about
Manchester United.

504
00:32:34,599 --> 00:32:36,079
It became toxic for a while.

505
00:32:39,159 --> 00:32:42,559
And I'm saying to myself,
"Is he looking for a war?"

506
00:32:42,919 --> 00:32:44,759
REPORTER:
Arsenal against Manchester United

507
00:32:44,839 --> 00:32:47,079
you expect their strongest side
to be playing today, obviously.

508
00:32:47,199 --> 00:32:49,679
HE CHUCKLES
Yes, you have a good sense of humor.

509
00:32:50,279 --> 00:32:53,399
When you're fighting to win,
you're two lions

510
00:32:53,719 --> 00:32:55,199
with only one desire

511
00:32:55,439 --> 00:32:57,679
is to eat the lion
who is against you.

512
00:33:00,159 --> 00:33:02,399
REPORTER: Brilliant, and let's have
some more of that today, thank you.

513
00:33:02,479 --> 00:33:03,319
Thank you. We'll try.

514
00:33:04,039 --> 00:33:07,439
I was not scared
of anybody in football.

515
00:33:11,199 --> 00:33:13,479
CROWD CHANTS AND CLAPS

516
00:33:18,079 --> 00:33:19,559
That game at Villa Park

517
00:33:19,799 --> 00:33:23,759
was the most emotional football match
I've ever played in.

518
00:33:23,879 --> 00:33:27,919
CROWD CHANTS

519
00:33:28,439 --> 00:33:30,639
We were going for a double,
another double...

520
00:33:30,799 --> 00:33:32,519
and United were going for the treble.

521
00:33:34,679 --> 00:33:36,119
People say,
"Do you miss the game?"

522
00:33:36,479 --> 00:33:38,439
I don't miss the game,
but I miss the big games.

523
00:33:38,919 --> 00:33:41,079
CROWD CLAMORS

524
00:33:43,079 --> 00:33:45,599
The Man United players were ready
to die for their club.

525
00:33:46,119 --> 00:33:47,959
COMMENTATOR:
Sheringham... for Beckham...

526
00:33:48,119 --> 00:33:49,679
Oh! What a goal!

527
00:33:52,119 --> 00:33:54,119
We were sure that
we were gonna win the game.

528
00:33:54,839 --> 00:33:57,759
COMMENTATOR: Bergkamp's shot...
deflected off Stam, it's in!

529
00:33:59,519 --> 00:34:00,959
FERGUSON:
We got Keane sent off.

530
00:34:01,119 --> 00:34:03,279
CROWD JEERS

531
00:34:03,359 --> 00:34:04,919
The drama was unbelievable.

532
00:34:05,559 --> 00:34:07,039
BERGKAMP:
We were 11 against 10.

533
00:34:07,719 --> 00:34:08,919
We just went for it.

534
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:11,599
COMMENTATOR:
Parlour's gone down!

535
00:34:14,599 --> 00:34:17,199
WENGER: In the 93rd minute,
we had a penalty.

536
00:34:18,119 --> 00:34:20,559
Oh, I thought we were out.
I did, I thought we were out.

537
00:34:26,039 --> 00:34:27,119
WENGER:
The penalty...

538
00:34:27,319 --> 00:34:30,039
marked our relationship
with Manchester United.

539
00:34:30,959 --> 00:34:34,559
CROWD ROARS

540
00:34:34,879 --> 00:34:35,719
The duel.

541
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:44,239
VIEIRA: If there is a guy
that I would want to take the penalty

542
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:46,199
it would be Dennis.

543
00:34:47,519 --> 00:34:49,759
Penalty taker should always score.

544
00:34:51,439 --> 00:34:52,879
It would've been over for them.

545
00:34:53,999 --> 00:34:56,159
This is strange, but I kept thinking

546
00:34:56,599 --> 00:34:58,439
he was gonna put it
in the left hand corner.

547
00:34:59,439 --> 00:35:01,439
COMMENTATOR:
Bergkamp vs Schmeichel...

548
00:35:05,079 --> 00:35:07,639
CROWD CHEERS
- Oh, and Schmeichel's saved it!

549
00:35:11,479 --> 00:35:13,039
WENGER:
After that, Dennis Bergkamp

550
00:35:13,279 --> 00:35:15,639
never wanted to take a penalty again.

551
00:35:18,919 --> 00:35:21,119
VIEIRA:
Details make a difference.

552
00:35:22,119 --> 00:35:25,279
COMMENTATOR:
Vieira... only as far as Giggs...

553
00:35:25,519 --> 00:35:26,679
I lost that ball.

554
00:35:27,159 --> 00:35:28,159
I should've brought him down.

555
00:35:28,879 --> 00:35:30,159
COMMENTATOR:
He'll run at Keown...

556
00:35:30,239 --> 00:35:31,479
and he'll run at Dixon...

557
00:35:31,999 --> 00:35:34,439
Oh! What about that?

558
00:35:36,319 --> 00:35:39,079
DIXON: My heart just sank
to the lowest low.

559
00:35:39,199 --> 00:35:41,239
FINAL WHISTLE BLOWS

560
00:35:41,599 --> 00:35:44,159
CROWD ROARS

561
00:35:48,559 --> 00:35:50,439
FERGUSON: I don't know
if we'd have won the European Cup

562
00:35:50,719 --> 00:35:52,119
if we hadn't won that game.

563
00:35:52,519 --> 00:35:54,719
Maybe we were destined
to win the treble that year.

564
00:35:58,799 --> 00:36:01,679
WENGER: I'll never forget
the happiness of Man United

565
00:36:01,759 --> 00:36:03,319
when they beat us that night.

566
00:36:14,239 --> 00:36:17,199
I threw up sometimes
after the games when I lost.

567
00:36:19,879 --> 00:36:21,799
It hurt so much.

568
00:36:26,479 --> 00:36:29,799
I'm a perfectionist
and I'm very demanding with myself.

569
00:36:34,199 --> 00:36:36,239
When you lose a game,
you always know

570
00:36:36,319 --> 00:36:37,719
there was a way to win it.

571
00:36:41,599 --> 00:36:43,799
But the defeat remains with you forever.

572
00:36:50,079 --> 00:36:51,959
Women kill for love...

573
00:36:53,639 --> 00:36:56,399
and men kill
because they hate to lose.

574
00:37:05,239 --> 00:37:06,639
CHILDREN YELL
— WENGER: Hey.

575
00:37:06,719 --> 00:37:08,639
A chaque fois vous m'avez surpris.

576
00:37:09,639 --> 00:37:11,199
WENGER:
The way I saw the job

577
00:37:11,359 --> 00:37:14,639
is to influence people's lives
through values.

578
00:37:17,039 --> 00:37:18,679
The players must know

579
00:37:18,759 --> 00:37:22,199
that if they have a real big problem,
they can call me.

580
00:37:24,279 --> 00:37:27,599
If there are difficult times,
I am there for them.

581
00:37:28,719 --> 00:37:29,599
Like a father.

582
00:37:33,039 --> 00:37:38,359
(FRENCH)

583
00:37:44,439 --> 00:37:47,199
(FRENCH)
— CHILDREN: Merci!

584
00:37:53,879 --> 00:37:56,319
VIEIRA:
He has always protected me

585
00:37:57,439 --> 00:37:59,759
and when the manager is defending you

586
00:38:00,679 --> 00:38:01,879
you will die for him.

587
00:38:04,799 --> 00:38:06,479
(FRENCH)

588
00:38:06,799 --> 00:38:09,319
WENGER:
The manager is somebody who has to...

589
00:38:10,159 --> 00:38:11,479
think, "I am not important.”

590
00:38:11,840 --> 00:38:13,319
<i>Eh, là, là, là, là, là.</i>

591
00:38:15,639 --> 00:38:17,599
WENGER:
It's a special job on that front.

592
00:38:18,959 --> 00:38:21,639
It demands
a psychological transformation.

593
00:38:26,599 --> 00:38:29,039
KEOWN: His biggest joy
was to see players improve.

594
00:38:31,759 --> 00:38:34,279
The training of Arséne Wenger
was on another level.

595
00:38:35,159 --> 00:38:38,679
You know, this feeling of invincibility
came on day one.

596
00:38:41,199 --> 00:38:42,759
It was the calmness
that he brought.

597
00:38:45,439 --> 00:38:47,679
VIEIRA:
When you are talking to him

598
00:38:48,679 --> 00:38:51,639
he doesn't give you
this kind of superiority.

599
00:38:52,439 --> 00:38:54,039
(FRENCH)

600
00:39:01,439 --> 00:39:03,039
THEY CHATTER
- THEO LAUGHS

601
00:39:03,479 --> 00:39:05,399
This is why I say to young players

602
00:39:05,759 --> 00:39:07,719
"Choose the club by the manager."

603
00:39:12,039 --> 00:39:13,879
CHILDREN LAUGH

604
00:39:15,439 --> 00:39:16,719
VIEIRA:
Talk to the manager

605
00:39:17,239 --> 00:39:19,519
he will be the one
who will make you a better player.

606
00:39:26,079 --> 00:39:27,599
CHILDREN CHEER

607
00:39:32,199 --> 00:39:34,279
INDISTINCT CHATTER

608
00:39:39,999 --> 00:39:41,519
THIERRY HENRY:
Arséne changed my life.

609
00:39:44,239 --> 00:39:45,279
Thierry Henry.

610
00:39:47,119 --> 00:39:52,039
COMMENTATOR IN FRENCH:

611
00:39:52,119 --> 00:39:53,919
WENGER:
I knew that from a young age

612
00:39:53,999 --> 00:39:56,319
already he was... special.

613
00:39:58,919 --> 00:40:00,799
HENRY:
He gave me an opportunity to shine.

614
00:40:02,359 --> 00:40:04,239
I can never
thank him enough for that.

615
00:40:05,519 --> 00:40:08,479
FERGUSON: We looked at Henry,
he was outside-left at Monaco.

616
00:40:09,559 --> 00:40:11,719
But, you know,
I couldn't see him as a centre-forward.

617
00:40:12,839 --> 00:40:16,199
REPORTER: The French international
surplus to requirements at Juventus

618
00:40:16,399 --> 00:40:17,879
Wenger has got his man

619
00:40:18,119 --> 00:40:20,439
although he's cost Arsenal
a club-record fee.

620
00:40:20,839 --> 00:40:23,159
WENGER:
He had lost something

621
00:40:23,439 --> 00:40:25,999
that is, basically, belief.

622
00:40:27,919 --> 00:40:30,519
The big change they made
at Arsenal was...

623
00:40:31,519 --> 00:40:32,919
reinventing Henry.

624
00:40:33,519 --> 00:40:36,319
And the goals...
I mean, he was fantastic.

625
00:40:38,479 --> 00:40:41,879
COMMENTATOR:
Oh... Oh! What a goal!

626
00:40:41,959 --> 00:40:43,759
Thierry Henry!

627
00:40:44,999 --> 00:40:47,039
I wasn't a centre-forward really

628
00:40:47,239 --> 00:40:48,399
when you watch me play.

629
00:40:49,919 --> 00:40:50,959
COMMENTATOR:
Henry...

630
00:40:51,319 --> 00:40:52,719
Henry!

631
00:40:53,799 --> 00:40:55,279
HENRY:
Arséne gave me that freedom.

632
00:40:55,399 --> 00:40:57,199
REPORTER: This role up front,
how are you enjoying it?

633
00:40:57,279 --> 00:40:58,199
HE CHUCKLES

634
00:41:00,559 --> 00:41:03,559
People in life arrive quite early

635
00:41:03,639 --> 00:41:06,479
at a very good level
and don't move too much

636
00:41:06,799 --> 00:41:08,799
because they don't
push themselves enough.

637
00:41:09,679 --> 00:41:11,879
You can be
a professional football player

638
00:41:11,959 --> 00:41:14,519
but I do want to discover
something more

639
00:41:14,599 --> 00:41:17,519
and explore, really,
what football can give you.

640
00:41:17,999 --> 00:41:19,599
COMMENTATOR:
Thierry Henry!

641
00:41:19,679 --> 00:41:21,079
Wonderful goal!

642
00:41:21,919 --> 00:41:24,119
HENRY:
The boss, in that way, is magnificent.

643
00:41:25,079 --> 00:41:27,119
He makes you realise
how good you can be.

644
00:41:27,919 --> 00:41:29,879
He allowed me to express myself.

645
00:41:32,519 --> 00:41:34,559
WRIGHT: When you look at
what he's done with Thierry

646
00:41:35,399 --> 00:41:36,759
it was frightening.

647
00:41:39,799 --> 00:41:41,759
COMMENTATOR:
You can only stand and admire.

648
00:41:42,519 --> 00:41:45,279
WRIGHT: Thierry Henry is the best
player that Arsenal has ever had.

649
00:41:56,719 --> 00:42:01,359
ROBERT PIRES IN FRENCH:

650
00:42:13,559 --> 00:42:16,959
VIEIRA:
London was really open-minded.

651
00:42:18,719 --> 00:42:20,679
People really don't care about...

652
00:42:21,239 --> 00:42:23,039
what you're driving,
what you're wearing

653
00:42:23,199 --> 00:42:24,479
or the color of your skin.

654
00:42:25,159 --> 00:42:26,319
THEY LAUGH

655
00:42:27,119 --> 00:42:28,839
IN FRENCH:

656
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:36,679
WENGER:
In the 2000s

657
00:42:37,319 --> 00:42:39,919
the foreign influence
in the culture of England

658
00:42:40,239 --> 00:42:43,079
politically and on
the footballing front

659
00:42:43,679 --> 00:42:46,159
started to become very important.

660
00:42:46,439 --> 00:42:48,199
HENRY:
Look at the post. Should've been a goal.

661
00:42:48,319 --> 00:42:50,039
<i>- Over the line.
- BOB WILSON: It was over, yeah.</i>

662
00:42:50,559 --> 00:42:51,799
Yeah! Ask Bob!

663
00:42:52,639 --> 00:42:56,239
WENGER: We moved from a monocultural
team to a multicultural team.

664
00:42:57,079 --> 00:43:00,119
Influences from all over Europe.

665
00:43:02,479 --> 00:43:04,639
It was as well
the evolution of the game

666
00:43:04,799 --> 00:43:07,359
because it was more mobile,
more technical

667
00:43:07,719 --> 00:43:09,759
more inspirational.

668
00:43:11,839 --> 00:43:14,879
BERGKAMP: He was a fan
of the Dutch Total Football...

669
00:43:16,199 --> 00:43:18,279
and I could see a lot
of similarities there.

670
00:43:19,439 --> 00:43:22,159
We really started to play football

671
00:43:22,239 --> 00:43:24,439
the way he saw football.

672
00:43:26,359 --> 00:43:27,559
Va-va-voom.

673
00:43:33,319 --> 00:43:34,719
WENGER:
I am a romantic.

674
00:43:36,519 --> 00:43:37,959
A pragmatic romantic.

675
00:43:42,239 --> 00:43:43,799
We are in entertainment.

676
00:43:45,639 --> 00:43:47,279
The groundwork is to win.

677
00:43:48,079 --> 00:43:49,399
But that is not enough.

678
00:43:52,679 --> 00:43:54,439
You need the ambition
to give more.

679
00:43:59,759 --> 00:44:02,479
To go deeper into what the game
can give to people.

680
00:44:03,639 --> 00:44:05,039
— Fingers crossed.
- Ta-ta.

681
00:44:05,119 --> 00:44:07,239
WOMAN: Cheers, mate. Bye.
-WOMAN 2: See ya!

682
00:44:08,119 --> 00:44:09,599
WENGER:
To get something more

683
00:44:09,759 --> 00:44:11,999
than just the individual expression
of a player.

684
00:44:12,119 --> 00:44:13,519
Gonna watch the champions tonight?

685
00:44:14,919 --> 00:44:17,959
WENGER:
But the collective expression of the team

686
00:44:18,959 --> 00:44:21,159
to transform it into art.

687
00:44:25,079 --> 00:44:26,679
WENGER:
You can say it's naive

688
00:44:27,239 --> 00:44:30,519
but you need to give
something special to people

689
00:44:30,759 --> 00:44:33,359
to get out of their hard daily life.

690
00:44:35,679 --> 00:44:37,759
COMMENTATOR:
It is nigh on perfect!

691
00:44:40,239 --> 00:44:42,639
CROWD CHANTS

692
00:44:43,119 --> 00:44:45,999
WENGER: I just wanted them
to sit in that seat

693
00:44:46,399 --> 00:44:47,359
and think...

694
00:44:48,639 --> 00:44:49,639
"Unbelievable."

695
00:44:50,119 --> 00:44:51,359
COMMENTATOR:
Freddie Ljungberg!

696
00:44:51,519 --> 00:44:53,439
CROWD ROARS

697
00:44:57,159 --> 00:44:59,959
COMMENTATOR: This is Bergkamp...
oh, wonderful skill from Dennis Bergkamp!

698
00:45:00,519 --> 00:45:02,239
What a superb goal!

699
00:45:02,879 --> 00:45:04,039
Pires...

700
00:45:04,119 --> 00:45:06,119
he's in here,
still Robert Pires...

701
00:45:06,679 --> 00:45:08,559
oh, what a wonderful goal!
- CAR HORN TOOTS

702
00:45:12,799 --> 00:45:14,039
WENGER:
2002...

703
00:45:14,679 --> 00:45:17,799
maybe we played
the most spectacular football ever.

704
00:45:18,519 --> 00:45:19,959
COMMENTATOR:
And Ljungberg...

705
00:45:20,159 --> 00:45:22,239
He's in again! Pushed out by Barthez!

706
00:45:22,439 --> 00:45:23,879
Wiltord!
- CROWD ROARS

707
00:45:26,479 --> 00:45:29,639
They've taken the title away
from Manchester United.

708
00:45:32,879 --> 00:45:34,639
WENGER:
You need to have that desire

709
00:45:35,959 --> 00:45:37,319
to give something more.

710
00:45:38,519 --> 00:45:41,839
CROWD CHANTS AND SINGS

711
00:45:41,959 --> 00:45:44,799
FANS SING: We won the league
in Manchester

712
00:45:45,199 --> 00:45:47,839
We won the league
and cup double

713
00:45:48,199 --> 00:45:50,639
We won the league in Manchester.

714
00:45:50,839 --> 00:45:53,159
WHISTLES BLOW
- HORNS TOOT

715
00:45:55,159 --> 00:45:58,199
CROWD CHANTS
- HORNS BLARE

716
00:46:02,559 --> 00:46:04,559
WENGER:
The influence you have on people's lives

717
00:46:04,639 --> 00:46:06,599
is to show them a little light

718
00:46:06,799 --> 00:46:08,439
of what is their next level.

719
00:46:10,999 --> 00:46:12,559
To go for something bigger.

720
00:46:14,039 --> 00:46:16,079
So in 2002...

721
00:46:17,279 --> 00:46:18,279
I set them a target

722
00:46:18,359 --> 00:46:20,959
and that was to win the Championship
without losing a game.

723
00:46:21,039 --> 00:46:22,319
CROWD ROARS

724
00:46:23,159 --> 00:46:25,119
THEY LAUGH

725
00:46:25,239 --> 00:46:28,279
We said, "He's losing his mind,
he's losing his head.

726
00:46:28,359 --> 00:46:29,599
What is he talking about?"

727
00:46:29,679 --> 00:46:32,159
I looked at the TV,
I was like, "Why?"

728
00:46:32,919 --> 00:46:34,839
(FRENCH)

729
00:46:34,999 --> 00:46:37,679
Of course, the media had
a real go at me

730
00:46:37,759 --> 00:46:39,439
they think it was arrogant.

731
00:46:39,519 --> 00:46:41,599
JOURNALIST: Did you say
“I want to go the whole season unbeaten"?

732
00:46:41,679 --> 00:46:42,999
JOURNALIST 2:
Do you think it's possible...

733
00:46:43,079 --> 00:46:44,359
<i>JOURNALIST 3:
Is that record within your grasp?</i>

734
00:46:44,479 --> 00:46:46,999
JOURNALIST 4: Do you regret saying
you could go the whole season unbeaten?

735
00:46:47,079 --> 00:46:48,999
WENGER:
I have no regrets at all about that.

736
00:46:52,079 --> 00:46:53,999
We didn't win the Championship.

737
00:46:57,279 --> 00:46:59,239
So I told them again

738
00:46:59,399 --> 00:47:00,999
"I still think you can do it"

739
00:47:01,799 --> 00:47:05,439
because I was so much attacked
by everybody

740
00:47:05,839 --> 00:47:08,359
that I thought, "Really, this time,
we have to do it."

741
00:47:08,439 --> 00:47:09,599
HE CHUCKLES

742
00:47:18,039 --> 00:47:19,999
HORSES CLOP

743
00:47:21,119 --> 00:47:23,799
INDISTINCT CHATTER

744
00:47:35,159 --> 00:47:37,919
VIEIRA:
He had this kind of vision about...

745
00:47:38,319 --> 00:47:40,079
what this team can achieve

746
00:47:40,399 --> 00:47:42,519
putting all our strengths together.

747
00:47:43,999 --> 00:47:46,959
Thinking that we would go through
the season unbeaten

748
00:47:47,159 --> 00:47:49,999
was something
that not even crossed our minds.

749
00:47:50,639 --> 00:47:52,039
He must've weighed that up.

750
00:47:52,879 --> 00:47:54,759
You know, the consequences
of saying that publicly

751
00:47:54,879 --> 00:47:56,399
but he genuinely believed that.

752
00:47:57,879 --> 00:47:59,879
And that's
what Arséne was trying to do.

753
00:48:00,679 --> 00:48:01,919
"Are we capable?"

754
00:48:05,759 --> 00:48:07,479
WENGER:
I had the ambition to do it.

755
00:48:08,399 --> 00:48:09,599
COMMENTATOR:
Now Henry...

756
00:48:10,119 --> 00:48:11,319
brilliant save!

757
00:48:12,079 --> 00:48:13,359
Pires! Goal!

758
00:48:15,239 --> 00:48:16,919
And I had the doubt as well.

759
00:48:25,719 --> 00:48:27,599
To get impossible targets...

760
00:48:28,799 --> 00:48:30,359
put the seed in their brains...

761
00:48:30,999 --> 00:48:32,839
and wait until it comes out.

762
00:48:40,519 --> 00:48:43,639
The more the dream
looks impossible

763
00:48:45,159 --> 00:48:47,599
the more it can strengthen
your motivation.

764
00:48:52,159 --> 00:48:54,879
THUNDER RUMBLES

765
00:49:02,639 --> 00:49:04,559
JOURNALIST: There's no love lost
between the two sides

766
00:49:04,639 --> 00:49:06,719
are you concerned
that the match itself

767
00:49:06,999 --> 00:49:08,759
could degenerate
in any shape or form?

768
00:49:09,839 --> 00:49:10,999
WENGER:
No, not at all.

769
00:49:12,919 --> 00:49:15,319
FERGUSON: Now, these are the kind
of games that come back to haunt you.

770
00:49:17,799 --> 00:49:19,639
It was us and Arsenal,
us and Arsenal.

771
00:49:20,759 --> 00:49:22,999
I think the intensity
between both clubs

772
00:49:23,279 --> 00:49:24,879
meant we knew we had
to beat each other.

773
00:49:25,279 --> 00:49:28,679
You know if you go
to Man United, you cannot lose

774
00:49:29,399 --> 00:49:31,039
if you want to win
the Championship.

775
00:49:31,959 --> 00:49:34,199
CROWD CLAMORS IN DISTANCE

776
00:49:49,719 --> 00:49:52,279
I liked it because the football
was rougher.

777
00:49:52,999 --> 00:49:55,039
The challenges were tougher.

778
00:49:55,359 --> 00:49:56,759
WHISTLE BLOWS

779
00:49:58,439 --> 00:50:00,999
It was a question of
"It's you or me."

780
00:50:04,119 --> 00:50:06,159
You can't leave you character
in the dressing room.

781
00:50:06,279 --> 00:50:07,519
It goes out on the pitch with you

782
00:50:08,319 --> 00:50:10,239
and Arsenal had to compete with that

783
00:50:10,599 --> 00:50:11,839
and they did very well at it.

784
00:50:13,879 --> 00:50:15,639
VIEIRA:
It went to a different level

785
00:50:15,799 --> 00:50:18,199
because they are feeling that...

786
00:50:19,279 --> 00:50:20,519
we are close to them.

787
00:50:20,599 --> 00:50:22,399
CROWD ROARS
- WHISTLE BLOWS

788
00:50:23,799 --> 00:50:24,919
And there was an incident.

789
00:50:26,039 --> 00:50:27,319
WHISTLE BLOWS

790
00:50:28,639 --> 00:50:30,039
COMMENTATOR:
Vieira kicking out there!

791
00:50:30,399 --> 00:50:32,199
WENGER: Van Nistelrooy
made more of it

792
00:50:32,639 --> 00:50:34,559
than it was, of course.

793
00:50:35,079 --> 00:50:37,639
But it was normal. It was United.
HE LAUGHS

794
00:50:37,719 --> 00:50:38,999
Patrick tried to kick him.

795
00:50:39,159 --> 00:50:40,919
COMMENTATOR:
Steve Bennett thinks that he did.

796
00:50:41,639 --> 00:50:43,399
Even though
he didn't make contact

797
00:50:43,519 --> 00:50:45,399
the intent was there.

798
00:50:46,559 --> 00:50:48,879
COMMENTATOR: He's off!
- CROWD CHEERS

799
00:50:54,959 --> 00:50:57,119
VIEIRA:
I was so mad, I was so...

800
00:51:01,079 --> 00:51:02,559
crazy in my head that...

801
00:51:04,519 --> 00:51:07,959
I was against the referee
and United.

802
00:51:08,519 --> 00:51:10,639
CROWD BOOS

803
00:51:13,359 --> 00:51:14,799
Then we had to survive.

804
00:51:17,319 --> 00:51:19,119
KEOWN:
The game changed completely.

805
00:51:19,719 --> 00:51:21,719
You don't wanna be the weakness,
you don't wanna be the weak link.

806
00:51:23,719 --> 00:51:24,999
You don't wanna let anyone down.

807
00:51:26,199 --> 00:51:27,799
<i>COMMENTATOR:
In towards Forlan...</i>

808
00:51:28,639 --> 00:51:30,519
Manchester United want a penalty...

809
00:51:30,599 --> 00:51:33,279
WHISTLE BLOWS
- ...and they've got one!

810
00:51:34,879 --> 00:51:36,159
KEOWN:
I've given the penalty away.

811
00:51:38,239 --> 00:51:39,119
It's all on me.

812
00:51:43,399 --> 00:51:45,679
I was thinking it's a robbery.

813
00:51:46,719 --> 00:51:48,279
We can lose this game now.

814
00:51:48,879 --> 00:51:50,079
It's unbelievable.

815
00:51:51,159 --> 00:51:58,679
(FRENCH)

816
00:51:59,079 --> 00:52:00,119
Never had a doubt when

817
00:52:00,199 --> 00:52:02,479
Van Nistelrooy had to take
an important penalty.

818
00:52:02,919 --> 00:52:04,279
100% confident.

819
00:52:14,599 --> 00:52:15,879
WENGER:
What did I say?

820
00:52:18,439 --> 00:52:19,399
Destiny.

821
00:52:22,399 --> 00:52:25,159
At that moment,
you have no control.

822
00:52:27,399 --> 00:52:29,199
The moment controls you.

823
00:52:29,719 --> 00:52:31,279
WHISTLE BLOWS
- COMMENTATOR: The responsibility rests

824
00:52:31,359 --> 00:52:33,519
with Ruud Van Nistelrooy.

825
00:52:34,999 --> 00:52:36,919
WENGER:
Life is about millimeters...

826
00:52:38,359 --> 00:52:39,639
about timing.

827
00:52:47,639 --> 00:52:49,079
COMMENTATOR:
Oh! He's missed it!

828
00:52:55,399 --> 00:52:56,439
He hit the bar.

829
00:52:57,239 --> 00:52:58,279
Justice.

830
00:53:01,879 --> 00:53:04,559
But that was not
the end of it, you know.

831
00:53:04,679 --> 00:53:07,039
FINAL WHISTLE BLOWS
- COMMENTATOR: It's the final whistle.

832
00:53:07,799 --> 00:53:09,999
And Arsenal do get their draw.

833
00:53:11,599 --> 00:53:12,799
All hell broke loose.

834
00:53:13,119 --> 00:53:14,679
FINAL WHISTLE BLOWS

835
00:53:16,199 --> 00:53:18,919
FERGUSON: They all had a target
on Ruud Van Nistelrooy.

836
00:53:19,719 --> 00:53:20,839
We let him have it.

837
00:53:22,479 --> 00:53:25,239
WENGER: I don't know what went
through the head of Martin Keown.

838
00:53:25,719 --> 00:53:28,279
PIRES:

839
00:53:37,359 --> 00:53:38,439
I loved it.

840
00:53:39,119 --> 00:53:40,119
I loved it.

841
00:53:42,799 --> 00:53:46,279
People always say that's too aggressive,
people always say that's not football

842
00:53:47,039 --> 00:53:50,039
but that was I think
an image of

843
00:53:50,359 --> 00:53:51,839
who we were as a team.

844
00:53:54,799 --> 00:53:57,359
It's not just about
the talent that we had.

845
00:53:58,759 --> 00:53:59,959
We could go to war.

846
00:54:02,559 --> 00:54:03,639
The FA will be looking at that.

847
00:54:05,159 --> 00:54:07,199
I think the FA will be
looking at all of the incidents

848
00:54:07,279 --> 00:54:08,359
at the end of the game.

849
00:54:14,319 --> 00:54:15,599
WENGER:
Martin Keown told me

850
00:54:15,679 --> 00:54:16,999
"I am ashamed, I am ashamed

851
00:54:17,079 --> 00:54:19,719
because my kids see that
on television."

852
00:54:20,439 --> 00:54:22,519
I said, "You didn't do nothing wrong.

853
00:54:22,799 --> 00:54:25,159
Don't worry, we will defend you".

854
00:54:25,279 --> 00:54:26,199
CAMERAS CLICK

855
00:54:26,279 --> 00:54:29,239
REPORTER: <i>The FA have charged Arsenal
for failing to control their players</i>

856
00:54:29,359 --> 00:54:32,439
while six members of the squad are
also individually charged

857
00:54:32,519 --> 00:54:33,519
with misconduct.

858
00:54:34,079 --> 00:54:36,919
The club has been fined £175,000

859
00:54:36,999 --> 00:54:38,999
and warned about its future behaviour.

860
00:54:40,239 --> 00:54:43,879
DEIN: It was a record fine
and a record ban.

861
00:54:47,199 --> 00:54:50,359
FANS CHANT:
Same old Arsenal, always cheating.

862
00:54:50,639 --> 00:54:53,799
Same old Arsenal, always cheating.

863
00:54:54,159 --> 00:54:56,839
Same old Arsenal, always cheating.

864
00:55:00,079 --> 00:55:01,999
BERGKAMP:
You wanna have an enemy, as a team.

865
00:55:02,599 --> 00:55:03,999
You wanna blame someone.

866
00:55:04,199 --> 00:55:05,599
Anyone who punished us.

867
00:55:06,239 --> 00:55:07,599
COMMENTATOR:
This is Aliadiere...

868
00:55:07,759 --> 00:55:08,879
and now Edu...

869
00:55:09,359 --> 00:55:11,759
We had each other's back.

870
00:55:13,959 --> 00:55:15,039
...Pires...

871
00:55:16,319 --> 00:55:17,999
oh, it's a fabulous shot!

872
00:55:18,079 --> 00:55:20,319
And a wonderful goal
by Robert Pires!

873
00:55:21,119 --> 00:55:23,039
Arsenal lead at Anfield.

874
00:55:23,479 --> 00:55:25,319
CROWD CHEERS

875
00:55:25,439 --> 00:55:30,879
(FRENCH)

876
00:55:35,319 --> 00:55:38,759
WENGER: It created a sense
of unity inside the team.

877
00:55:40,199 --> 00:55:41,839
It strengthened our desire.

878
00:55:42,119 --> 00:55:44,599
PLAYERS YELL AND CHEER

879
00:55:47,159 --> 00:55:48,839
We didn't say goodbye
to a title.

880
00:56:04,719 --> 00:56:07,479
(FRENCH)

881
00:56:11,359 --> 00:56:12,519
WENGER:
I traveled around the world

882
00:56:12,599 --> 00:56:14,919
my brother
didn't want to leave his village.

883
00:56:17,319 --> 00:56:18,759
And football was not a job.

884
00:56:19,639 --> 00:56:22,359
Football is something you do
when you don't work.

885
00:56:27,679 --> 00:56:30,759
FERGUSON: People brought up
in these areas have a foundation.

886
00:56:31,799 --> 00:56:33,719
The discipline and the work rate...

887
00:56:36,039 --> 00:56:39,319
There's something that's driven
inside Arséne that said, "Well

888
00:56:39,959 --> 00:56:41,159
I want better than this."

889
00:56:43,159 --> 00:56:49,159
BERNADETTE:

890
00:56:53,919 --> 00:56:56,639
WENGER: My parents came
to watch Arsenal specially

891
00:56:56,719 --> 00:56:57,999
when I won my first double.

892
00:56:59,279 --> 00:57:01,959
After that,
it was a bit more difficult.

893
00:57:03,919 --> 00:57:07,519
My father maybe contributed more
than you'd think.

894
00:57:08,719 --> 00:57:11,599
He never told me, "Well done".

895
00:57:12,559 --> 00:57:13,519
No.

896
00:57:14,759 --> 00:57:16,399
He said, "You can do better".

897
00:57:17,479 --> 00:57:19,359
That strive for perfection

898
00:57:19,439 --> 00:57:22,199
that desire to do well
certainly comes from him.

899
00:57:25,999 --> 00:57:28,199
At that time,
you educated people

900
00:57:28,279 --> 00:57:30,199
to work hard, to give their best

901
00:57:30,839 --> 00:57:32,999
and to be ready to suffer.

902
00:57:35,239 --> 00:57:37,679
FERGUSON: This creates
a certain stubbornness about you

903
00:57:37,799 --> 00:57:39,399
that you know
where you've come from.

904
00:57:39,679 --> 00:57:42,519
That working-class ethic
is gonna be there all the time.

905
00:57:52,439 --> 00:57:54,479
WENGER:
Contrary to what people think

906
00:57:55,359 --> 00:57:59,359
the 2004 season
was not the Rolls Royce season.

907
00:58:02,599 --> 00:58:04,519
I was not sure that we could

908
00:58:04,799 --> 00:58:06,959
continue the whole season unbeaten.

909
00:58:08,239 --> 00:58:11,279
COMMENTATOR: ...and the whistle goes.
Arsenal have hung on.

910
00:58:12,439 --> 00:58:13,759
WENGER:
You have to prepare.

911
00:58:14,039 --> 00:58:16,559
You go out on a stormy night.

912
00:58:17,599 --> 00:58:18,559
COMMENTATOR:
Bolton Wanderers...

913
00:58:18,639 --> 00:58:21,079
unfortunate not to have taken
all three points.

914
00:58:23,679 --> 00:58:26,519
WENGER: Show me that you can go home
without losing a game.

915
00:58:30,239 --> 00:58:32,919
I think it's a real definition
of humility.

916
00:58:33,159 --> 00:58:34,759
CROWD CHEERS

917
00:58:34,879 --> 00:58:36,959
COMMENTATOR:
A mammoth psychological boost.

918
00:58:37,159 --> 00:58:39,799
A huge win at Highbury for Arsenal.

919
00:58:42,199 --> 00:58:45,879
HENRY: Highbury,
in those hard moments gave us...

920
00:58:46,919 --> 00:58:47,799
everything.

921
00:58:48,759 --> 00:58:49,919
Life...

922
00:58:50,679 --> 00:58:51,639
power...

923
00:58:52,239 --> 00:58:53,519
will, desire.

924
00:58:54,399 --> 00:58:56,999
FANS SING:
Arsenal

925
00:58:57,279 --> 00:59:00,199
Arsenal FC.

926
00:59:02,359 --> 00:59:04,439
WENGER: There is something special
about Highbury.

927
00:59:05,639 --> 00:59:06,879
I still go back.

928
00:59:10,319 --> 00:59:13,359
When you're half a mile away,
you still don't see the stadium.

929
00:59:13,799 --> 00:59:16,159
INDISTINCT STREET CHATTER

930
00:59:17,879 --> 00:59:19,119
You look down...

931
00:59:19,519 --> 00:59:22,479
you see already the fans
waiting for you.

932
00:59:23,399 --> 00:59:26,119
FANS CHANT:
Arsenal, Arsenal, Arsenal.

933
00:59:26,239 --> 00:59:29,919
WENGER: You go out of your coach
and you go through your supporters.

934
00:59:30,639 --> 00:59:33,359
FANS CHEER AND APPLAUD

935
00:59:37,319 --> 00:59:39,639
Everything was small,
the corridors were small.

936
00:59:42,359 --> 00:59:46,119
But all the ancestors had
their spirit in there.

937
00:59:46,199 --> 00:59:47,239
Are you OK?

938
00:59:53,919 --> 00:59:55,839
When you took a corner at Highbury

939
00:59:55,919 --> 00:59:57,759
you could shake the hand
of the fans.

940
00:59:58,879 --> 01:00:00,879
You could speak
with the supporters.

941
01:00:03,759 --> 01:00:04,919
Or worse, you know.

942
01:00:07,599 --> 01:00:08,599
After games

943
01:00:08,679 --> 01:00:11,879
the fans knew we were in the dressing room
with the connection on the wall.

944
01:00:11,999 --> 01:00:13,559
PLAYERS LAUGH

945
01:00:13,839 --> 01:00:16,199
The players responded
by opening the window.

946
01:00:17,239 --> 01:00:19,359
So I had Ian Wright
shouting with the fans

947
01:00:19,439 --> 01:00:21,559
<i>"I will see you when I come out,"
you know?</i>

948
01:00:28,399 --> 01:00:31,599
Sometimes I need to have
that feeling again, you know?

949
01:00:31,879 --> 01:00:34,799
And I go up the road
and go down, like before.

950
01:00:38,559 --> 01:00:39,719
It was real.

951
01:00:40,359 --> 01:00:42,919
And you cannot find that back

952
01:00:43,199 --> 01:00:44,799
when you build a new stadium.

953
01:00:49,519 --> 01:00:52,399
REPORTER: Arsenal are planning
to move out of historic Highbury

954
01:00:52,479 --> 01:00:54,119
REPORTER 2:
Arsenal spent years of planning

955
01:00:54,199 --> 01:00:55,399
and millions of pounds

956
01:00:55,479 --> 01:00:57,639
on a plan to move
to a new stadium.

957
01:01:02,599 --> 01:01:05,079
DEIN: We had to move.
There was no doubt about it.

958
01:01:06,799 --> 01:01:09,719
We had a wait list of
about 50,000 people for tickets.

959
01:01:11,079 --> 01:01:13,039
I could see ourselves left behind.

960
01:01:15,439 --> 01:01:17,479
FANS SING:
Chelsea, Chelsea.

961
01:01:17,759 --> 01:01:21,199
Chelsea, Chelsea,
Chelsea, Chelsea.

962
01:01:21,399 --> 01:01:23,599
Chelsea, Chelsea, Chelsea

963
01:01:26,239 --> 01:01:27,239
WENGER:
During that season

964
01:01:27,319 --> 01:01:29,799
Chelsea was, for a long period,
top of the league.

965
01:01:32,439 --> 01:01:33,879
Abramovich came in...

966
01:01:36,319 --> 01:01:38,119
and there was no financial fair play.

967
01:01:39,079 --> 01:01:41,519
REPORTER: The biggest spending spree
in footballing history...

968
01:01:41,599 --> 01:01:43,719
REPORTER 2:
76 million pounds' worth of talent

969
01:01:43,959 --> 01:01:46,359
to bring the Premiership title
to West London.

970
01:01:48,439 --> 01:01:50,919
WENGER: It was the ideal moment
to buy football clubs

971
01:01:50,999 --> 01:01:52,639
because you could do
what you wanted.

972
01:01:56,199 --> 01:01:57,479
I told the players

973
01:01:57,839 --> 01:01:58,879
"It's now or never."

974
01:01:58,959 --> 01:02:00,319
FAN:
Go on, Chelsea!

975
01:02:03,439 --> 01:02:05,079
KEOWN:
Wenger had got it to fever pitch.

976
01:02:06,119 --> 01:02:08,919
FANS SING:
Come on Chelsea, Come on Chelsea.

977
01:02:09,719 --> 01:02:11,799
You didn't wanna be
in the team that lost.

978
01:02:15,199 --> 01:02:16,839
COMMENTATOR:
Bergkamp... Vieira...

979
01:02:18,999 --> 01:02:20,679
<i>a captain's contribution!</i>

980
01:02:21,079 --> 01:02:22,959
CO-COMMENTATOR:
They've absolutely carved them open.

981
01:02:23,319 --> 01:02:25,199
WENGER: The vibes
coming out of the team

982
01:02:25,639 --> 01:02:27,759
are always dictated by the fans.

983
01:02:29,039 --> 01:02:31,479
They know if it's a real team
out there.

984
01:02:33,159 --> 01:02:34,199
COMMENTATOR:
Edu puts it in!

985
01:02:34,479 --> 01:02:36,559
It's all happened inside 20 minutes!

986
01:02:37,839 --> 01:02:39,199
BERGKAMP:
When you're at the top

987
01:02:39,279 --> 01:02:41,799
you wanna show the ones
who wanna take over

988
01:02:42,799 --> 01:02:44,359
"Wait a minute,
it's not your turn yet

989
01:02:44,439 --> 01:02:45,559
we're still here".

990
01:02:45,639 --> 01:02:47,079
And that's what we did.

991
01:03:07,999 --> 01:03:09,719
WENGER:
I have the addiction gene.

992
01:03:12,559 --> 01:03:13,839
One negative side effect

993
01:03:13,919 --> 01:03:17,799
is that you don't develop
some aspects of your personality

994
01:03:17,879 --> 01:03:19,479
that you could have developed
in your life.

995
01:03:23,159 --> 01:03:27,119
More sensitivity, more caring
about people.

996
01:03:29,159 --> 01:03:32,559
That's where my daughter started
at school.

997
01:03:33,439 --> 01:03:34,719
And this school

998
01:03:35,159 --> 01:03:39,119
has seen the Premier League trophy
and the FA Cup.

999
01:03:44,119 --> 01:03:45,359
I feel guilty.

1000
01:03:46,999 --> 01:03:49,679
My passion created selfishness.

1001
01:03:52,119 --> 01:03:53,079
WENGER IN INTERVIEW:
Every night.

1002
01:03:53,719 --> 01:03:56,119
Like I have my dinner,
I have my football game.

1003
01:03:59,199 --> 01:04:02,399
Sometimes of course, on Sundays,
you have so many games that uh...

1004
01:04:02,799 --> 01:04:05,439
in the end, you go to bed,
you don't know what you have seen anymore.

1005
01:04:08,879 --> 01:04:10,439
My passion made me

1006
01:04:10,759 --> 01:04:13,159
not to take care enough
of people around me.

1007
01:04:16,119 --> 01:04:18,799
I would've loved
to have a bigger family.

1008
01:04:19,479 --> 01:04:22,239
And the fact that I was
so focused on football

1009
01:04:22,679 --> 01:04:24,639
I'm today very grateful

1010
01:04:24,799 --> 01:04:25,839
to have a daughter.

1011
01:04:29,039 --> 01:04:32,919
Certainly,
my balance was too much in favour

1012
01:04:33,359 --> 01:04:36,319
of the club and not enough
in favour of my family.

1013
01:04:40,599 --> 01:04:42,439
I try to repair that now.

1014
01:04:42,559 --> 01:04:43,919
HE CHUCKLES

1015
01:04:48,039 --> 01:04:50,479
Competition at all costs

1016
01:04:50,719 --> 01:04:54,079
is something that destroys
a part of your personality.

1017
01:04:56,279 --> 01:04:58,599
This desire of hating to lose

1018
01:04:58,879 --> 01:05:01,639
makes you sometimes
somebody inhuman.

1019
01:05:22,239 --> 01:05:25,559
HENRY: At the time,
we were going for the treble.

1020
01:05:28,319 --> 01:05:30,159
WRIGHT:
Arséne Wenger, mentally...

1021
01:05:31,159 --> 01:05:34,119
would've been one of
the hardest weeks in his football career.

1022
01:05:35,919 --> 01:05:37,999
KEOWN:
We had a week of trauma.

1023
01:05:38,959 --> 01:05:39,999
Madness.

1024
01:05:44,559 --> 01:05:45,879
WENGER:
I made a mistake.

1025
01:05:46,999 --> 01:05:49,999
I played the regular team
cos it was Man United.

1026
01:05:50,199 --> 01:05:52,159
CROWD ROARS
- COMMENTATOR: It's Ryan Giggs!

1027
01:05:52,279 --> 01:05:53,919
Back to Scholes!

1028
01:05:55,399 --> 01:05:57,599
The treble dream is over.

1029
01:06:00,399 --> 01:06:02,359
WENGER:
We went into the Chelsea game

1030
01:06:02,759 --> 01:06:04,439
physically diminished.

1031
01:06:05,559 --> 01:06:08,719
CROWD CLAMORS

1032
01:06:08,999 --> 01:06:09,879
We collapsed.

1033
01:06:10,839 --> 01:06:12,719
COMMENTATOR:
Wayne Bridge could win it... he has!

1034
01:06:16,959 --> 01:06:18,239
WRIGHT:
Going out the FA Cup

1035
01:06:18,319 --> 01:06:19,479
going out of the Champions League

1036
01:06:20,239 --> 01:06:22,359
and the pressure of being
The Invincibles.

1037
01:06:24,119 --> 01:06:25,479
WENGER:
You go very quickly

1038
01:06:25,639 --> 01:06:27,919
into confidence crisis.

1039
01:06:30,639 --> 01:06:32,879
Every loss becomes more difficult

1040
01:06:33,119 --> 01:06:34,719
to repair the damage done.

1041
01:06:44,479 --> 01:06:46,759
HENRY: There is so much happening
in the season

1042
01:06:46,839 --> 01:06:49,359
that people do not... know.

1043
01:06:50,039 --> 01:06:52,719
REPORTER: <i>Arsenal's World
has turned upside down this week.</i>

1044
01:06:53,399 --> 01:06:55,559
HENRY: It was taboo
to talk about mental health.

1045
01:06:56,439 --> 01:06:59,359
JOURNALIST:

1046
01:07:00,279 --> 01:07:02,199
Do you know the amount of pressure
that you have to go through

1047
01:07:02,279 --> 01:07:03,199
during a season?

1048
01:07:03,519 --> 01:07:06,399
Because you're the go-to guy,
because you're the coach.

1049
01:07:08,359 --> 01:07:09,999
WENGER:
You have such a crazy schedule

1050
01:07:10,079 --> 01:07:13,399
that if it was today,
it would be a big, big blow.

1051
01:07:17,399 --> 01:07:19,919
Liverpool, 2004. Good Friday.

1052
01:07:21,639 --> 01:07:23,799
The decisive moment of that season.

1053
01:07:36,599 --> 01:07:38,479
I still can remember today

1054
01:07:38,679 --> 01:07:40,119
that tension in the stadium.

1055
01:07:42,959 --> 01:07:45,279
COMMENTATOR:
And turned in by Sami Hyypiä!

1056
01:07:50,479 --> 01:07:51,839
HENRY:
When Michael Owen scored

1057
01:07:53,119 --> 01:07:54,919
I felt like Highbury died.

1058
01:07:55,519 --> 01:07:56,639
COMMENTATOR:
Gerrard...

1059
01:07:57,359 --> 01:07:59,159
oh and he's picked out
Michael Owen!

1060
01:08:02,759 --> 01:08:04,719
CROWD WHISTLES AND JEERS

1061
01:08:06,959 --> 01:08:08,759
I felt like something was gone.

1062
01:08:08,999 --> 01:08:10,679
HALF TIME WHISTLE BLOWS

1063
01:08:12,799 --> 01:08:13,999
WENGER:
We were in shock.

1064
01:08:19,039 --> 01:08:21,119
How quickly you can go from

1065
01:08:21,519 --> 01:08:23,599
being on a high to a low,
it was unbelievable

1066
01:08:23,679 --> 01:08:24,879
in four or five days.

1067
01:08:29,279 --> 01:08:31,239
KEOWN: I've never been
in a dressing room that was so low.

1068
01:08:33,999 --> 01:08:35,519
Down, hurt, wounded.

1069
01:08:40,799 --> 01:08:44,079
WENGER:
The manager can reduce crisis time.

1070
01:08:46,119 --> 01:08:47,919
That is something very important.

1071
01:08:50,439 --> 01:08:53,519
"Invincible" is linked
with a mental resilience.

1072
01:08:55,359 --> 01:08:56,999
It is something deeper.

1073
01:09:01,439 --> 01:09:03,959
A refusal of defeat at any costs.

1074
01:09:06,039 --> 01:09:08,759
CROWD CHEERS AND ROARS

1075
01:09:09,239 --> 01:09:11,199
Don't give in ever.

1076
01:09:14,759 --> 01:09:17,399
All I can remember is me
coming out of the tunnel.

1077
01:09:18,919 --> 01:09:20,559
I just wanted to go back on the field

1078
01:09:20,639 --> 01:09:22,199
and rectify what had been done.

1079
01:09:23,879 --> 01:09:25,439
WENGER:
The special players

1080
01:09:25,519 --> 01:09:27,999
they find solutions at the moment
where you need them.

1081
01:09:28,199 --> 01:09:29,079
<i>Wow, let's go.</i>

1082
01:09:29,399 --> 01:09:30,639
CROWD CLAMORS

1083
01:09:30,759 --> 01:09:31,879
COMMENTATOR:
Henry...

1084
01:09:33,439 --> 01:09:35,559
past Hamann,
who got nowhere near him...

1085
01:09:35,679 --> 01:09:37,319
For him to come up
with a goal like that

1086
01:09:37,399 --> 01:09:39,359
in a game like that,
after a week like that...

1087
01:09:39,879 --> 01:09:40,919
it was Superman stuff.

1088
01:09:41,079 --> 01:09:42,959
...and still going, Thierry Henry!

1089
01:09:44,799 --> 01:09:46,159
When I took that ball

1090
01:09:46,359 --> 01:09:48,519
I said to myself,
"I'm going to goal

1091
01:09:48,599 --> 01:09:50,039
no matter what."

1092
01:09:51,879 --> 01:09:54,159
COMMENTATOR: Running at Hamann,
and away from him...

1093
01:09:54,479 --> 01:09:56,519
running at Carragher,
and away from him!

1094
01:09:56,599 --> 01:09:58,159
Still Thierry Henry!

1095
01:09:58,359 --> 01:10:00,479
Fantastic goal!
- CROWD CHEERS

1096
01:10:03,479 --> 01:10:06,839
A simply sensational solo effort!

1097
01:10:07,279 --> 01:10:08,519
HENRY:
When I scored that goal

1098
01:10:08,759 --> 01:10:10,599
I felt like we all scored it.

1099
01:10:11,919 --> 01:10:13,759
And I felt like everything came back

1100
01:10:14,759 --> 01:10:16,399
to a...
HE EXHALES DEEPLY

1101
01:10:16,959 --> 01:10:19,839
COMMENTATOR: Dennis Bergkamp,
lifted over the top for Thierry Henry...

1102
01:10:20,319 --> 01:10:23,519
WENGER: It was just like a machine
working on full cylinders again.

1103
01:10:24,319 --> 01:10:27,279
COMMENTATOR: And all the traumas
of the week are left behind!

1104
01:10:31,759 --> 01:10:34,159
WENGER:
We had passed the doubt period

1105
01:10:35,159 --> 01:10:36,719
come back to full strength.

1106
01:10:40,479 --> 01:10:41,519
Wow.

1107
01:10:42,839 --> 01:10:46,319
CROWD CHANTS INDISTINCTLY

1108
01:10:47,959 --> 01:10:50,279
REPORTER: Do they have
the word "choking” in French?

1109
01:10:50,399 --> 01:10:53,119
That's not the kind of word
I have in my dictionary, so...

1110
01:10:53,199 --> 01:10:54,279
REPORTER:
I didn't think it was.

1111
01:10:54,359 --> 01:10:56,839
FANS SING:
Are you watching? Are you watching?.

1112
01:10:56,959 --> 01:10:58,839
Are you watching, Tottenham?

1113
01:10:58,959 --> 01:11:01,559
Are you watching, Tottenham?

1114
01:11:07,919 --> 01:11:09,399
WENGER:
Just before the game

1115
01:11:09,759 --> 01:11:13,039
we knew that with a draw
we were champions.

1116
01:11:20,119 --> 01:11:22,399
FANS SING:
Me love you Arsenal, we do...

1117
01:11:22,919 --> 01:11:28,919
IN FRENCH:

1118
01:11:36,199 --> 01:11:37,999
COMMENTATOR:
Henry... look at that

1119
01:11:38,399 --> 01:11:39,639
away from Redknapp...

1120
01:11:40,239 --> 01:11:41,679
BERGKAMP:
We knew exactly from each other

1121
01:11:41,759 --> 01:11:43,639
where we would play
on the pitch.

1122
01:11:44,759 --> 01:11:46,959
<i>COMMENTATOR: Pires in the middle...
it's Dennis Bergkamp</i>

1123
01:11:47,159 --> 01:11:48,359
and Vieira

1124
01:11:48,479 --> 01:11:50,519
FANS YELL AND CHEER

1125
01:11:51,639 --> 01:11:53,319
Everyone knew what to do.

1126
01:11:53,679 --> 01:11:55,399
FANS YELL AND CHEER

1127
01:11:55,679 --> 01:11:57,039
That's an amazing feeling.

1128
01:11:58,719 --> 01:11:59,839
COMMENTATOR:
Bergkamp...

1129
01:12:00,719 --> 01:12:01,759
<i>here's Vieira...</i>

1130
01:12:02,279 --> 01:12:04,719
and Robert Pires makes it two!

1131
01:12:05,119 --> 01:12:07,239
It's brilliant from Arsenal!

1132
01:12:10,519 --> 01:12:12,719
BERGKAMP:
This football is close to perfection.

1133
01:12:15,479 --> 01:12:17,399
That summed up Arséne's vision.

1134
01:12:19,039 --> 01:12:20,079
What a pleasure.

1135
01:12:20,799 --> 01:12:22,639
HE LAUGHS

1136
01:12:22,719 --> 01:12:25,159
FINAL WHISTLE BLOWS
- CROWD CHEERS

1137
01:12:25,239 --> 01:12:27,519
COMMENTATOR:
And Arsenal are champions.

1138
01:12:27,679 --> 01:12:30,479
FANS CHEER AND SHOUT

1139
01:12:30,639 --> 01:12:33,159
WENGER:
This team was a perfect mixture

1140
01:12:33,439 --> 01:12:37,119
of continental influence
on the way to see football

1141
01:12:37,519 --> 01:12:41,079
but in a British environment
and with British cultures.

1142
01:12:41,399 --> 01:12:43,319
FANS CHEER

1143
01:12:46,519 --> 01:12:50,919
Perfect immigration by respecting
local values.

1144
01:12:51,159 --> 01:12:53,039
Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh!

1145
01:12:53,119 --> 01:12:55,559
Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh!

1146
01:12:55,639 --> 01:12:57,039
Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh!

1147
01:12:59,079 --> 01:13:01,559
WENGER BREATHES HEAVILY

1148
01:13:05,599 --> 01:13:07,559
WENGER: I told them,
"It's down to you now.

1149
01:13:11,439 --> 01:13:12,759
If you want to ease off

1150
01:13:13,119 --> 01:13:16,599
and just accept that you become
a normal human being

1151
01:13:16,679 --> 01:13:18,359
once he has achieved something...

1152
01:13:23,279 --> 01:13:25,679
or do you want to do something special...

1153
01:13:28,839 --> 01:13:30,479
COMMENTATOR:
It's Reyes!

1154
01:13:31,759 --> 01:13:33,039
...become immortal?"

1155
01:13:45,879 --> 01:13:47,439
KEOWN:
It was another day in the sun.

1156
01:13:48,159 --> 01:13:49,319
The trophy's there.

1157
01:13:50,119 --> 01:13:51,759
CROWD CHEERS

1158
01:13:52,079 --> 01:13:53,359
We go a goal down.

1159
01:13:55,319 --> 01:13:58,319
IN FRENCH:

1160
01:14:04,799 --> 01:14:06,119
WHISTLE BLOWS

1161
01:14:06,879 --> 01:14:08,039
CROWD CHEERS

1162
01:14:12,919 --> 01:14:16,079
WENGER: There is something symbolic
in Patrick Vieira's destiny.

1163
01:14:17,399 --> 01:14:21,799
COMMENTATOR: Magic ball
from Bergkamp to Patrick Vieira!

1164
01:14:22,959 --> 01:14:24,959
WENGER:
People questioned me when I arrived.

1165
01:14:26,119 --> 01:14:28,079
The first player I bought was Patrick.

1166
01:14:29,359 --> 01:14:30,439
What a player.

1167
01:14:31,759 --> 01:14:33,279
COMMENTATOR:
The build-up begins...

1168
01:14:34,359 --> 01:14:36,679
to a magical, magical moment.

1169
01:14:36,839 --> 01:14:38,679
FINAL WHISTLE BLOWS
- CROWD CHEERS

1170
01:14:38,839 --> 01:14:44,199
Arsenal have gone through
an entire league campaign without losing.

1171
01:14:46,799 --> 01:14:49,199
HE BREATHES HEAVILY

1172
01:14:49,319 --> 01:14:52,239
CONFETTI CANNONS BOOM
- CROWD CHEERS

1173
01:15:01,319 --> 01:15:02,439
VIEIRA:
You never know...

1174
01:15:02,879 --> 01:15:05,199
how good you are,
you never know where you can go

1175
01:15:05,519 --> 01:15:07,479
and I think this team will be
remembered forever now.

1176
01:15:10,839 --> 01:15:12,719
It was just one big joy.

1177
01:15:14,639 --> 01:15:16,839
It was fantastic to be part of it.

1178
01:15:17,719 --> 01:15:19,719
It's the highest that you can achieve
as a team.

1179
01:15:21,279 --> 01:15:23,959
HENRY:
We all became individually invincible

1180
01:15:24,519 --> 01:15:26,959
but we are "Invincibles".

1181
01:15:27,679 --> 01:15:30,199
To be able to achieve that,
it's second to none.

1182
01:15:31,159 --> 01:15:32,919
REPORTER: "I think we can go
the whole season unbeaten”

1183
01:15:32,999 --> 01:15:34,439
well, he was a man ahead of himself,
wasn't he?

1184
01:15:34,519 --> 01:15:37,879
He said that 18 months ago
and today he's finally been proved right.

1185
01:15:44,319 --> 01:15:45,959
WENGER:
It was the moment

1186
01:15:46,519 --> 01:15:48,839
where I fulfilled the dream of my life.

1187
01:15:54,479 --> 01:15:57,199
The fact that I could convince this group

1188
01:15:57,359 --> 01:15:59,319
to achieve something that they...

1189
01:16:00,119 --> 01:16:01,999
would not think
would be possible.

1190
01:16:04,239 --> 01:16:07,759
I've done my job in a perfect way
one year...

1191
01:16:10,479 --> 01:16:12,839
and I'm so proud for having done it.

1192
01:16:25,879 --> 01:16:28,879
DISTANT CHANTS ECHO

1193
01:16:47,559 --> 01:16:49,199
INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER

1194
01:16:53,879 --> 01:16:55,319
WENGER:
Look well at the pitch here

1195
01:16:55,439 --> 01:16:58,479
that's the pitch where we'll make
a disaster in a few minutes.

1196
01:17:03,279 --> 01:17:04,999
Sometimes I wonder...

1197
01:17:06,039 --> 01:17:09,399
was something broken
after that invincible season?

1198
01:17:14,639 --> 01:17:17,799
Because I had done
what I really wanted deeply.

1199
01:17:19,319 --> 01:17:22,399
PLAYERS YELL INDISTINCTLY

1200
01:17:23,719 --> 01:17:24,919
Is it a symbol?

1201
01:17:27,159 --> 01:17:28,319
Is it linked with me?

1202
01:17:28,399 --> 01:17:32,119
That after that, when I thought
I had achieved the highest level

1203
01:17:32,239 --> 01:17:33,679
that I didn't do it again?

1204
01:17:37,679 --> 01:17:41,559
(FRENCH)

1205
01:17:42,639 --> 01:17:45,519
We were there,
and he was there, and...

1206
01:17:45,839 --> 01:17:49,079
we climbed up the mountain,
but, yeah... what now?

1207
01:17:52,959 --> 01:17:54,959
WENGER:
I meet many huge champions.

1208
01:17:55,959 --> 01:17:58,719
They talk to you
only about what they lost...

1209
01:18:00,719 --> 01:18:03,239
because success is easy to absorb

1210
01:18:03,879 --> 01:18:05,919
but the defeat remains forever.

1211
01:18:12,199 --> 01:18:13,399
Highbury...

1212
01:18:14,279 --> 01:18:15,159
my soul.

1213
01:18:15,239 --> 01:18:17,039
TRAIN RATTLES

1214
01:18:17,319 --> 01:18:18,399
The Emirates...

1215
01:18:19,479 --> 01:18:20,679
my suffering.

1216
01:18:24,239 --> 01:18:26,599
I could see that times
would be more difficult.

1217
01:18:28,239 --> 01:18:31,159
We started with a project
at over 200 million

1218
01:18:31,239 --> 01:18:32,799
that we could basically afford.

1219
01:18:34,679 --> 01:18:37,559
Then we finished at 428 million.

1220
01:18:40,199 --> 01:18:42,359
FERGUSON:
What it cost to get the new stadium...

1221
01:18:43,919 --> 01:18:45,199
it left them bare.

1222
01:18:50,519 --> 01:18:53,319
WENGER:
2007 was a decisive point.

1223
01:18:55,999 --> 01:18:57,039
OK.

1224
01:18:57,479 --> 01:19:01,039
It's the first time I could feel
there were tensions inside the board.

1225
01:19:03,399 --> 01:19:06,039
David Dein had an agreement
with Stan Kroenke

1226
01:19:06,119 --> 01:19:07,319
he wanted to bring in.

1227
01:19:08,119 --> 01:19:10,919
I was torn between
being loyal to the club

1228
01:19:11,439 --> 01:19:13,079
and being loyal to David.

1229
01:19:14,839 --> 01:19:16,199
He actually wanted to leave.

1230
01:19:17,119 --> 01:19:18,999
And I said to him...

1231
01:19:20,279 --> 01:19:21,599
"You have to stay, Arséne."

1232
01:19:25,879 --> 01:19:29,239
I still today wonder
if I did the right thing.

1233
01:19:30,879 --> 01:19:33,439
Because life was never
exactly the same after.

1234
01:19:35,039 --> 01:19:37,079
<i>REPORTER:
Arséne, you have some news to tell us.</i>

1235
01:19:37,159 --> 01:19:39,959
I extended my contract
with Arsenal Football Club.

1236
01:19:40,919 --> 01:19:42,919
That is some good news
for you, I hope.

1237
01:19:43,359 --> 01:19:44,639
It's good news for me.

1238
01:19:47,279 --> 01:19:50,319
I thought, "I have now
to go to the end of this project."

1239
01:19:52,679 --> 01:19:54,759
I could've gone
to the French national team

1240
01:19:54,839 --> 01:19:57,719
the English national team twice
or three times, even.

1241
01:19:58,439 --> 01:20:00,399
I could've gone twice
to Real Madrid.

1242
01:20:00,799 --> 01:20:03,679
I could've gone to Juventus,
to Paris Saint Germain

1243
01:20:03,879 --> 01:20:04,999
even to Man United.

1244
01:20:05,239 --> 01:20:06,999
Very good, very good, very good.

1245
01:20:07,799 --> 01:20:10,039
My fatal flaw is that...

1246
01:20:11,159 --> 01:20:13,519
I love too much where I am.

1247
01:20:16,279 --> 01:20:17,319
Where I was.

1248
01:20:24,399 --> 01:20:25,719
HENRY:
It's gonna be difficult.

1249
01:20:25,999 --> 01:20:26,919
Man!

1250
01:20:27,519 --> 01:20:29,319
WENGER:
Once we moved into the stadium

1251
01:20:29,399 --> 01:20:32,039
between one and two,
we moved to three and four.

1252
01:20:33,439 --> 01:20:35,039
We lost our best players.

1253
01:20:35,839 --> 01:20:37,039
HENRY:
After Mr Dein left

1254
01:20:37,119 --> 01:20:40,759
I needed to be certain
of where the club was going

1255
01:20:40,839 --> 01:20:44,039
and I wasn't,
and I've chosen to go.

1256
01:20:45,199 --> 01:20:47,199
WENGER:
Before, we lost them at 30 plus.

1257
01:20:47,639 --> 01:20:49,879
After, we lost them at 25 plus.

1258
01:20:51,039 --> 01:20:52,239
HE EXHALES

1259
01:20:55,639 --> 01:20:57,999
To work with restricted resources

1260
01:20:58,079 --> 01:21:01,239
and keep the club in a position
where we can pay our debts back.

1261
01:21:02,519 --> 01:21:05,279
From 2006 to 2015

1262
01:21:05,439 --> 01:21:07,399
I personally think I did my best job.

1263
01:21:08,919 --> 01:21:11,239
KEOWN: There's lots of reasons,
financial reasons

1264
01:21:11,319 --> 01:21:13,359
board struggles,
the new stadium...

1265
01:21:14,439 --> 01:21:16,319
but I think he almost
became a bit addicted

1266
01:21:16,399 --> 01:21:18,239
to wanting to prove
he could win another Premier League.

1267
01:21:20,839 --> 01:21:23,599
WENGER: To be stubborn
can be a strength and a weakness.

1268
01:21:23,959 --> 01:21:25,919
FAN: Wenger won't change his tactics.
He won't change it, fam!

1269
01:21:25,999 --> 01:21:28,679
FAN 2: Not in a title race,
season after season.

1270
01:21:28,919 --> 01:21:30,759
If anything, we 're going backwards.

1271
01:21:30,839 --> 01:21:33,559
Without strong beliefs,
you do nothing in life

1272
01:21:34,039 --> 01:21:36,759
because you change every day,
you go one day right and one day left.

1273
01:21:39,119 --> 01:21:41,599
CROWD CHEERS

1274
01:21:43,039 --> 01:21:46,359
I am the right man
to lead this club further, and that's it.

1275
01:21:48,479 --> 01:21:50,399
It's not about popularity

1276
01:21:50,599 --> 01:21:53,039
it's about competence.

1277
01:21:54,079 --> 01:21:55,759
PLAYERS YELL

1278
01:21:55,879 --> 01:21:57,839
WRIGHT: I think one
of his worst statements was

1279
01:21:57,919 --> 01:21:59,639
"Fourth is like a trophy".

1280
01:22:01,199 --> 01:22:03,079
KEOWN:
What we saw on the pitch changed.

1281
01:22:04,079 --> 01:22:06,279
It became very technical,
almost too technical.

1282
01:22:07,519 --> 01:22:10,159
Yes, he could've gone
on many occasions, but he didn't.

1283
01:22:11,159 --> 01:22:13,559
And Arsenal gave
a lot to him as well.

1284
01:22:18,839 --> 01:22:21,119
WRIGHT:
The game against Chelsea...

1285
01:22:21,759 --> 01:22:23,399
it was his 1000th game.

1286
01:22:25,199 --> 01:22:27,079
CROWD CHEERS

1287
01:22:28,079 --> 01:22:29,879
6-0 the final score in that game.

1288
01:22:32,159 --> 01:22:33,919
The greatest manager
in Arsenal's history

1289
01:22:33,999 --> 01:22:35,879
and the players perform like that.

1290
01:22:36,239 --> 01:22:37,719
PIERS MORGAN:
How many of this team

1291
01:22:37,799 --> 01:22:40,879
<i>would get in The Invincibles or
either of Wenger's double-winning teams?</i>

1292
01:22:41,519 --> 01:22:42,599
Zero.

1293
01:22:42,959 --> 01:22:44,999
There didn't seem to be
any accountability

1294
01:22:45,079 --> 01:22:46,559
for people who played poorly.

1295
01:22:47,119 --> 01:22:49,399
They took his kindness for weakness.

1296
01:22:51,559 --> 01:22:55,239
HENRY:
The boss had that magnificent attribute

1297
01:22:55,359 --> 01:22:57,519
of seeing the good always.

1298
01:22:57,919 --> 01:22:59,239
But at one point also

1299
01:22:59,399 --> 01:23:01,919
you need to see what you have
and what's happening.

1300
01:23:02,999 --> 01:23:05,799
FANS CHANT:
No new contract, no new contract.

1301
01:23:05,999 --> 01:23:08,719
No new contract, no new contract.

1302
01:23:09,319 --> 01:23:11,079
<i>COMMENTATOR:
Arséne Wenger, he's not happy</i>

1303
01:23:11,159 --> 01:23:13,599
he seems to be getting more and more
wound up at every decision.

1304
01:23:14,639 --> 01:23:15,759
DIXON:
It was horrible.

1305
01:23:16,199 --> 01:23:17,359
The fall from grace

1306
01:23:18,079 --> 01:23:19,759
but it's his own making in the end.

1307
01:23:21,279 --> 01:23:24,559
Arsenal had its hooks in Arséne

1308
01:23:24,879 --> 01:23:26,679
and he couldn't break free.

1309
01:23:26,919 --> 01:23:30,119
FANS CHANT: Where's our money gone?
Where's our money gone?

1310
01:23:30,239 --> 01:23:33,399
Me want our Arsenal back
We want our Arsenal back.

1311
01:23:33,479 --> 01:23:36,039
BERGKAMP:
That must not have been a nice period

1312
01:23:36,239 --> 01:23:39,119
but it's all down to doubt in his mind.

1313
01:23:40,159 --> 01:23:44,159
Maybe it would've been easier
if he would've made a decision.

1314
01:23:45,119 --> 01:23:46,799
FAN:
The power, the money...

1315
01:23:47,359 --> 01:23:50,119
he took that over what was best
for Arsenal Football Club.

1316
01:23:50,559 --> 01:23:52,879
COMMENTATOR:
More signs of Arsenal disgruntlement...

1317
01:23:53,199 --> 01:23:55,679
these have become
increasingly regular.

1318
01:23:55,879 --> 01:23:58,119
FANS CHANT: We want Wenger out,
say we want Wenger out.

1319
01:23:58,239 --> 01:24:00,279
WENGER:
I'm very demanding with myself.

1320
01:24:01,439 --> 01:24:03,519
I should have delegated more.

1321
01:24:04,679 --> 01:24:07,639
Have I lost the quality
of my judgment?

1322
01:24:07,879 --> 01:24:08,999
I don't know.

1323
01:24:09,359 --> 01:24:13,519
But my dedication,
my desire to do well

1324
01:24:14,119 --> 01:24:15,639
was exactly the same.

1325
01:24:15,759 --> 01:24:19,319
FANS SING:
We want Wenger out! Wenger out!

1326
01:24:21,039 --> 01:24:23,399
But I wish that you will see again

1327
01:24:23,959 --> 01:24:26,239
Arsenal 20 consecutive years

1328
01:24:26,319 --> 01:24:28,079
to qualify for the Champions League.

1329
01:24:28,159 --> 01:24:30,999
FANS CHANT:
No new contract! No new contract!

1330
01:24:31,159 --> 01:24:33,839
No new contract! No new contract!

1331
01:24:34,239 --> 01:24:35,919
He kept them in Europe every year.

1332
01:24:36,519 --> 01:24:37,599
You know...

1333
01:24:37,799 --> 01:24:40,239
And yet, he was criticized.

1334
01:24:41,959 --> 01:24:45,439
These supporters
maybe should be ashamed.

1335
01:24:48,239 --> 01:24:51,119
I thought in the...
some movies in Hollywood

1336
01:24:51,199 --> 01:24:53,439
where there's always a great ending

1337
01:24:53,559 --> 01:24:55,439
or Sir Alex,
that had a great ending.

1338
01:24:56,719 --> 01:24:59,039
Most of the time,
endings are not great.

1339
01:25:03,119 --> 01:25:04,839
NEWS PRESENTER:
Breaking news coming to us here

1340
01:25:04,919 --> 01:25:06,639
<i>Arséne Wenger,
the Arsenal manager</i>

1341
01:25:06,719 --> 01:25:09,519
<i>is to step down
at the end of the season.</i>

1342
01:25:18,119 --> 01:25:20,679
PRESS OFFICER: Hi, folks,
thanks for coming down on short notice

1343
01:25:20,759 --> 01:25:22,479
on what is obviously a memorable day

1344
01:25:22,999 --> 01:25:24,239
for Arsenal Football Club.

1345
01:25:25,119 --> 01:25:26,639
IVAN <i>GAZIDIS:
Arséne changed the game.</i>

1346
01:25:27,239 --> 01:25:29,879
He set a totally new standard.

1347
01:25:30,559 --> 01:25:33,319
And we will give him
the send-off he deserves.

1348
01:25:38,479 --> 01:25:40,039
INDISTINCT CHATTER:

1349
01:25:40,159 --> 01:25:42,959
WOMAN: How far do you want them apart?
— I just think width of the tunnel.

1350
01:25:43,079 --> 01:25:45,639
So then the boss is just literally
gonna walk out, clap

1351
01:25:46,159 --> 01:25:47,879
<i>and then it's normal match day.</i>

1352
01:25:48,639 --> 01:25:51,279
FANS CHEER

1353
01:25:56,239 --> 01:25:57,919
WENGER:
It's the end of your life.

1354
01:25:59,479 --> 01:26:00,959
At least of one life.

1355
01:26:03,839 --> 01:26:05,039
Like a funeral.

1356
01:26:06,279 --> 01:26:08,279
So after 22 years in charge

1357
01:26:08,359 --> 01:26:11,439
<i>how did you think you'd expect
to celebrate the emotions of the occasion?</i>

1358
01:26:11,599 --> 01:26:14,959
FANS SING: One Arséne Wenger!
There's only one Arsene Wenger.

1359
01:26:15,439 --> 01:26:18,159
One Arséne Wenger.

1360
01:26:22,919 --> 01:26:23,959
WENGER:
On the day...

1361
01:26:24,159 --> 01:26:25,759
everybody's nice with you

1362
01:26:26,119 --> 01:26:27,799
and one week before

1363
01:26:28,439 --> 01:26:30,519
you had to face
a lot of criticism.

1364
01:26:31,039 --> 01:26:33,799
Arsene Wenger, the visionary

1365
01:26:33,879 --> 01:26:35,799
Arsene Wenger, an inspiration.

1366
01:26:38,119 --> 01:26:42,799
(FRENCH)

1367
01:26:47,439 --> 01:26:49,919
ANNOUNCER:
One of football's biggest figures

1368
01:26:49,999 --> 01:26:51,759
in this global age of ours

1369
01:26:51,839 --> 01:26:55,599
and most importantly,
a special man.

1370
01:26:56,279 --> 01:26:57,319
VIEIRA:
Arsene...

1371
01:26:58,479 --> 01:26:59,799
left Arsenal...

1372
01:27:00,359 --> 01:27:01,399
out of the back door

1373
01:27:01,479 --> 01:27:04,359
but even not the back door,
I would say the back window.

1374
01:27:06,679 --> 01:27:09,399
ANNOUNCER:
This, then, is Arsene Wenger.

1375
01:27:10,079 --> 01:27:12,759
The greatest manager
we have ever had.

1376
01:27:12,919 --> 01:27:15,159
FANS APPLAUD AND CHEER

1377
01:27:17,399 --> 01:27:20,799
Please give him
the greatest welcome you can.

1378
01:27:21,359 --> 01:27:23,799
BYSTANDERS APPLAUD

1379
01:27:29,439 --> 01:27:31,439
WENGER:
You think about when you arrived...

1380
01:27:33,159 --> 01:27:34,959
all the players that you managed...

1381
01:27:37,239 --> 01:27:41,039
because you realise
that it's the end.

1382
01:27:42,439 --> 01:27:45,319
PLAYERS APPLAUD
- Thank you all very well

1383
01:27:45,999 --> 01:27:48,359
for having me
for such a long time.

1384
01:27:50,119 --> 01:27:51,599
I know that's not easy.

1385
01:27:54,599 --> 01:27:56,959
FANS CHANT INDISTINCTLY

1386
01:27:57,839 --> 01:27:59,199
I will miss you.

1387
01:27:59,559 --> 01:28:02,079
CROWD APPLAUDS

1388
01:28:02,719 --> 01:28:05,439
WENGER:
I managed to control my emotional side.

1389
01:28:11,279 --> 01:28:14,759
But of course,
the end of a love story

1390
01:28:15,399 --> 01:28:16,639
is always sad.

1391
01:28:19,959 --> 01:28:22,559
GAZIDIS: Arsene will always
have a place at the club.

1392
01:28:23,799 --> 01:28:27,439
Today it's too early to talk about
what that might look like down the road.

1393
01:28:30,159 --> 01:28:33,719
Thank you all for being
such an important part of my life

1394
01:28:34,079 --> 01:28:35,679
and hope to see you soon.

1395
01:28:35,839 --> 01:28:37,199
Well done. Bye-bye.

1396
01:28:37,519 --> 01:28:39,919
CROWD APPLAUDS AND CHEERS

1397
01:28:41,839 --> 01:28:44,399
FANS SING:
There's only one Arséne Wenger.

1398
01:28:44,839 --> 01:28:46,959
One Arséne Wenger.

1399
01:28:55,919 --> 01:28:57,039
WENGER:
I regret.

1400
01:29:00,279 --> 01:29:02,199
I should have gone somewhere else.

1401
01:29:04,599 --> 01:29:07,439
I identified myself completely
with the club

1402
01:29:07,519 --> 01:29:11,159
and that was the mistake I made.

1403
01:29:13,559 --> 01:29:17,399
Now there is no special reason
for me to go there.

1404
01:29:19,799 --> 01:29:23,519
All the rest is purely emotion...

1405
01:29:25,479 --> 01:29:27,679
and that is less important.

1406
01:29:29,999 --> 01:29:32,159
CHILDREN CHATTER INDISTINCTLY

1407
01:29:33,839 --> 01:29:36,279
INDISTINCT CHATTER

1408
01:29:38,359 --> 01:29:44,239
PHOTOGRAPHER:
- ALL:

1409
01:29:44,319 --> 01:29:46,679
BYSTANDERS APPLAUD

1410
01:29:48,559 --> 01:29:50,319
WENGER:
My village, they are proud

1411
01:29:50,839 --> 01:29:53,279
that they produced a guy who was

1412
01:29:53,359 --> 01:29:55,999
internationally-known
as a football man.

1413
01:29:56,639 --> 01:29:59,159
INDISTINCT CHATTER IN FRENCH

1414
01:30:00,279 --> 01:30:03,959
They think, rightly so, certainly
that they contributed to that.

1415
01:30:11,639 --> 01:30:14,359
If happiness is to love
the life that you lead

1416
01:30:14,719 --> 01:30:17,119
I was very happy
because I wanted this life.

1417
01:30:25,559 --> 01:30:26,999
I became less religious

1418
01:30:27,119 --> 01:30:30,359
but the importance
of spiritual values

1419
01:30:30,919 --> 01:30:32,319
was always present.

1420
01:30:35,919 --> 01:30:37,279
Even in a game

1421
01:30:37,479 --> 01:30:39,279
something that unites people

1422
01:30:39,759 --> 01:30:41,119
is more than the ball.

1423
01:30:43,839 --> 01:30:46,119
They are guided by something
bigger than that.

1424
01:30:49,199 --> 01:30:51,759
That makes them really be together.

1425
01:30:57,039 --> 01:31:01,639
COMMENTATOR: Magic ball
from Bergkamp to Patrick Vieira!

1426
01:31:05,719 --> 01:31:08,079
WENGER:
This team became invincible.

1427
01:31:08,879 --> 01:31:11,439
COMMENTATOR:
Fabulous shot! Wonderful goal!

1428
01:31:13,239 --> 01:31:14,879
WENGER:
They managed to achieve something

1429
01:31:14,959 --> 01:31:17,999
that they would not think possible.

1430
01:31:23,199 --> 01:31:25,759
You can have as much talent
as you want to

1431
01:31:26,519 --> 01:31:29,399
but what will make
a project successful

1432
01:31:29,839 --> 01:31:31,119
is always gonna be the people.

1433
01:31:33,159 --> 01:31:35,119
The one who put it together...

1434
01:31:36,359 --> 01:31:37,479
is Arsene.

1435
01:31:38,279 --> 01:31:40,199
He was the father of our project.

1436
01:31:42,039 --> 01:31:43,199
Invincible.

1437
01:31:44,239 --> 01:31:45,399
FERGUSON:
I loved those games.

1438
01:31:45,679 --> 01:31:47,519
Yeah, I loved those games
against Arsenal.

1439
01:31:47,759 --> 01:31:48,839
They were fantastic.

1440
01:31:57,319 --> 01:32:00,039
I think Arsene
and myself are dinosaurs.

1441
01:32:01,879 --> 01:32:03,359
We didn't do so badly.

1442
01:32:03,879 --> 01:32:06,799
CROWD CHEERS
- HORNS TOOT

1443
01:32:09,679 --> 01:32:11,319
I won 13 leagues

1444
01:32:11,839 --> 01:32:15,319
but I was never near
going through a season undefeated.

1445
01:32:20,279 --> 01:32:21,599
The achievement...

1446
01:32:22,119 --> 01:32:24,679
it stands aside.
It stands above everything else.

1447
01:32:24,959 --> 01:32:26,679
And it was Arsenal's.

1448
01:32:37,999 --> 01:32:40,119
WENGER:
I dream about football...

1449
01:32:42,919 --> 01:32:44,359
about what I have done.

1450
01:32:46,839 --> 01:32:49,519
Where did I do well?
Where did I not do well?

1451
01:32:52,599 --> 01:32:55,879
I couldn't believe
that football can be a job.

1452
01:32:57,319 --> 01:32:59,319
That, for me,
was on a different planet.

1453
01:33:02,879 --> 01:33:05,119
My life, on that front,
is a miracle.

1454
01:33:05,719 --> 01:33:07,599
CAMERAS CLICK

1455
01:33:08,799 --> 01:33:11,639
Fear guides the restriction
of our ambition.

1456
01:33:14,959 --> 01:33:16,839
You have not to be scared.

1457
01:33:18,919 --> 01:33:20,519
Be audacious...

1458
01:33:21,519 --> 01:33:22,999
be ambitious.

1459
01:33:25,119 --> 01:33:29,239
Your life can be wilder
than your wildest dream.

